title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in large plastic or glass bowl.
Stir together the sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Cook at medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Cook without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn; stir to coat well.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes. (Stir soon after putting in the oven.)
Break apart when cool. Enjoy!

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef in 1 tablespoon of butter along with green pepper and onion.
Cook noodles and drain.
Layer in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour remaining 3 tablespoons of melted butter over the top and bake at 350° until bubbly and hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable sandwich filling
directions: Put all vegetables through food grinder (don't use core of cucumber).
Blend with cream cheese and spread on bread for sandwiches.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen sandwiches.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Sprinkle in some cheese, a little at a time.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk, butter and beaten eggs.
Sprinkle top with leftover cheese.
Cook in 350° oven until top is golden brown.

title: creamy ham and noodle dinner
directions: In a small bowl combine flour and a small amount of milk until smooth. Add remaining milk, dill and mustard; set aside. In a large saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Add carrots and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally until crisp tender. Stir in reserved milk mixture; bring to a boil, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Cook and stir 1 minute. Stir in ham, noodles and peas. Cook and stir until heated through. Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut pineapple pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Melt margarine.
Cream in sugar; then blend in eggs.
Mix in drained pineapple and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk over low heat.
Stir constantly for 7 minutes after it comes to a boil.

title: brownie cheesecake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In mixer bowl, beat flour, sugar, melted butter, cocoa, 2 eggs, milk, 2 teaspoons vanilla and baking powder until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread into pan.

title: cream cheese topping
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a large kettle cook beef, onions, green peppers and garlic until meat is browned, drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: clara's cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar. Fold in chopped nuts and Corn Flakes; mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° until light brown, 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove while hot and cool on paper towel.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O and 1 c. HOT water.
Let stand.

title: savory hero
directions: Combine meat, tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Mix until well blended.
Spread half of meat mixture on each half of bread. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Top with layers of process cheese food, tomato and green pepper. Continue baking until cheese food melts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs in large bowl; add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts, apples and vanilla.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch or tube pan at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve as is or use topping.

title: salsa
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut into small chunks.
Put all ingredients in pan.
Cook and
simmer a couple of hours.
Freeze in bags.

title: green bean bake
directions: Combine 1/2 can of fried onions and remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake for 5 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring butter, water and salt to a boil until butter is melted. Put on low heat, add the flour, stir constantly.
When the mixture falls away from the sides of the pan, turn off heat.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat very, very well.
Drop one tablespoon of the mixture at a time on a greased baking sheet, leave plenty of room between each spoonful for the mixture to expand.
Bake at 400° for approximately 40 minutes, take out of oven and slice the top of each puff, return to the oven for approximately 5 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 large cream puffs.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat Crescent rolls in greased jelly roll pan, bake at 350 degrees until lightly browned.
Mix together Cream cheese, Mayonnaise, Dill Weed and Onion Salt and spread onto cooled crust. Cover with Chopped vegetables and cut into small squares.

title: fabulous pumpkin spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed 5 minutes.
Pour batter into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes, then loosen center and sides with plastic spatula.
Invert and place on wire rack to cool. Ice, if desired, with cream cheese frosting or glaze.

title: brownies
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and add 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in buttered pan at 350°.
While brownies are still warm, pour over the following icing.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
I usually chop the vegetables in a blender to be sure that all are chopped finely.
Cook over low heat at least 1/2 hour.
Stir occasionally as it tends to stick. Makes almost 1 quart of sauce.
Real good with chicken, ribs or beef.

title: american lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef and garlic in 1 tablespoon of hot fat. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Cook lasagna noodles (9 noodles) according to package directions.

title: after game hot dogs
directions: Cook oleo, pepper, Worcestershire, flour, mustard, tomato soup and celery until thick; add ground up hot dogs and heat through; add cheese.
Fill each hot dog bun, then wrap in foil and refrigerate until ready to use.
Heat in oven at 350° until hot, about 15 minutes.

title: pioneer coconut cake
directions: Blend all but last ingredient 3 to 4 minutes.
Fold in coconut.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to other mixture alternating with coconut and milk.
Pour into greased and floured pan (or use Pam). Bake in a 325° oven.
For tube pan bake 70 minutes; for 13 x 9-inch pan bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Rub iron skillet with bacon grease. Heat skillet. Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl; stir well. Pour mixture into hot skillet and bake about 30 minutes or until sides look brown and crispy.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix well in order given. Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: broccoli onion casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; set aside.
Cook onion in boiling salted water 10 minutes or until tender.
Set aside to drain. Melt 2 tablespoons butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Continue stirring and cook 2 more minutes.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in broccoli and onion.
When combined, turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with American cheese.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and toss with bread crumbs and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: devils food cake
directions: *Mix milk and 2 teaspoons vinegar.

title: salzkuchen(german bread)
directions: Place dough on large greased cookie sheet.
Saute onions (chopped) until clear.
Cool.
Combine sour cream, egg and caraway seed.
Add onions.
Spread evenly onto crust.
Salt liberally. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Topping looks set (kind of dry). Serve hot or cold.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: This is easy.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate one hour. Keep unused portions refrigerated.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add sour cream last. Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twenty four hour slaw
directions: Stir 1/2 cup sugar into cabbage and place half of this mixture in a large bowl. Cover with onion rings, then cover with remaining cabbage.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together one ingredient at a time.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.
Store in freezer until ready to serve.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt. Blend until mixture resembles fine crumbs like cornmeal. Sprinkle water over crumbs. Work
with fork in bowl. Let sit 10 minutes. Roll out on floured board and put in 9-inch pie pan.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl; mix well on medium speed. Bake in greased loaf pans.
Makes 2 large or 3 medium loaves. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Toss chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Heat butter and oil in large frypan and brown chicken in it.
Stir in garlic, cognac, tomatoes, marjoram, wine and bay leaf.
Cover and cook over low heat 25 minutes.
Add mushrooms and olives and cook 10 minutes longer, or until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle top with parsley. Serve with slices of French bread.
Rice is a good accompaniment. Amount of chicken breasts:
at least 1/2 breast each person. Great to make day before.
Refrigerate, then heat up to serve. This improves flavor.

title: mixed fruit smoothies
directions: In a blender container, cut up bananas, strawberries, grape juice, yogurt and if desired, honey. Cover and blend until smooth. Pour into 6 chilled glasses. If desired, garnish with additional strawberries and mango slices.

title: skillet chicken-rice curry
directions: Brown chicken in skillet, using a small amount of oil.
Add mushroom soup and 2 cans of water.
Add onion, celery seed, parsley, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 1/2 hours on low. Add rice 15 minutes before done, mixing well with sauce.
Add more water, if necessary.
Serve chicken pieces on a bed of rice.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Saute beef and sausage together until well done.
Drain.
Add cheese and other ingredients.
Spread on party rye bread and bake for a few minutes until hot and crisp.
Makes about 6 to 8 dozen. Mixture can be frozen.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: In large roaster layer peeled and cut up fairly small pieces of potatoes.
Crumble hamburger over potatoes.
Spread mixed vegetables over hamburger.
Pour beefy mushroom soup over the vegetables.
Slice (pour) Cheddar cheese over the layered mixture. Cover and bake for 2 to 3 hours at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers and set aside 1/4 cup chopped green pepper.
Cut x into bottom of whole peppers.
Cook whole peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Salt inside of peppers and set aside.

title: cheese and rye
directions: Mix cheese and onions together with enough mayonnaise to spread.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Spread evenly on rye rounds and place on baking sheet.
Broil until bubbly and barely beginning to brown.
Watch closely.

title: microwave creole hamburger
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart glass casserole dish. Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix with ground beef.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes longer.
Serve over noodles.
Good over rice if desired.

title: artichoke mini-bagels
directions: Mix artichoke hearts, mayonnaise and cheese together; blend well. Slice bagels down the middle and spread each half with artichoke mixture. Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut in pieces; place in a large pan. Chop peppers and garlic; cut onions in long slices. Combine all ingredients. Cover and heat over low heat until tender. Put in hot sterilized jars and seal immediately.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Melt margarine and
mix with flour and chopped nuts for crust. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool.

title: company chicken
directions: Bone each chicken breast and wrap a strip of bacon around it. Salt and pepper to taste.
Line casserole with smoked beef.
Place chicken on top of the beef.
Mix the sour cream with the soup. Pour over the chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients and add to egg and sugar mixture.
Add oil and sour cream.
Beat well. Stir in apples, pecans and vanilla.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let cool in pans for 5 minutes.
Turn out on a wire rack and finish cooling. Makes two loaves.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate 24 hours or more. Keeps 2 weeks.
Drain before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs plus vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa 3 times.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Blend in food coloring.
Dissolve soda in vinegar.
Fold into batter.
Bake in 3 layers in a 350° oven.

title: peach pudding
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and egg yolks in double boiler until thick, about 10 minutes. Cool. Put vanilla wafers in bottom of pan, pour custard over wafers. Next, put peaches (sliced) over custard. Put Cool Whip on top.

title: cauliflower au gratin soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, heat margarine until bubbly and hot; add onion and saute until golden. Add cauliflower, water, broth mix and nutmeg; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer until cauliflower is tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly.
Pour half of cauliflower mixture into blender container and, using an on-off motion, process at low speed until cauliflower is finely chopped (do not puree).
Transfer mixture to medium bowl and repeat procedure with remaining cauliflower mixture; return chopped cauliflower mixture to saucepan.
Add milk and half and half and heat (do not boil).

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in brown sugar and oats.
Mix in egg, butter, milk and apple.
Fill greased muffin tins.
Sprinkle tops with mixture of 4 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 25 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: apple betty
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with orange juice.
Combine sugar, flour and spices.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is crisp.
Very good served with vanilla ice cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a heavy sauce pan.
Bring to a rolling boil and heat for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the marshmallow creme and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour into a buttered 9 inch x 12 inch pan.

title: easy sandwich spread
directions: Shred Spam into bowl.
Chop boiled eggs into Spam.
Add cheese and Miracle Whip.

title: viennese coffee
directions: Pour the coffee into a stemmed glass and top with a dollop of whipped cream.
Dust the cream with ground cinnamon, cloves or nutmeg, if desired.
Serve at once.

title: apple julep
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients with ice cubes; mix will. Garnish each serving with mint.

title: rolo cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl mix flour, cocoa and baking soda; mix well.
In large bowl beat 1 cup sugar, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs, beat well. Add flour mixture, blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
For each cookie, with floured hands, shape about 1 tablespoon dough around 1 caramel candy, cover completely.
In small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup pecans and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Press 1 side of each ball into pecan mixture.
Place nut side up, 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until set and slightly cracked.
Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheets.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sugar, butter, flour, well beaten egg, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix thoroughly.
Put into greased baking dish and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
Marshmallows may be placed on top with done and browned slightly.

title: beef and vegetable fried rice
directions: In large non-stick skillet, brown beef, garlic and ginger over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, breaking up into 3/4-inch crumbles.

title: lasagne
directions: Beat egg and add to Mozzarella cheese.
Layer noodles, beef, sauce and cheese mix to fill a baking dish.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Watch carefully toward end of cooking time and don't let cheese on top burn, just brown a little.
Remove from oven and let it set for about 5 minutes to let the cheese cool down.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook, cube and peel potatoes.
Blend together mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serves 20 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Mix cocoa and water; then mix together with sugar and eggs.
Add butter, mix well.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: marinated antipasto tray
directions: In a small bowl or jar, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, water, garlic, hot pepper sauce and salad dressing mix.
Mix well.

title: potato chip casserole
directions: Combine meat, celery and onions. Place half of mixture in casserole dish.
Spoon half of soup and 1/4 cup water over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup potato chips.
Repeat layers in the same order.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, onions, peppers and other ingredients.
Let come to a boil or until pears are done, but not soft. Add more peppers, if needed. Put in jars and seal.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Mixture will be thick.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Place biscuits in greased cupcake tin.
Press to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon 1/4 cup meat mixture into each cup.
Top with cheese.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.

title: copper carrots
directions: Peel carrots and slice round.
Put them in water and cook until tender.
Drain carrots, then put pepper and onions into a large bowl and salt and pepper to taste.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Sift flour and cocoa together; set aside.
Melt butter; mix sugar, butter and eggs together.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add flour mixture and stir until well mixed.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake for about 25 minutes.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Brown stewing beef in skillet with oil.
Put in crock-pot. Pour drained mushrooms on top of beef.
Put soups on top of mushrooms.
Cover and cook over low setting 10 to 14 hours.
Serve over prepared noodles.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water. Add broccoli and cook until soft, about 5 minutes. Add soups and mix well. Add cheese, salt and pepper. Cook on low and let it thicken. Enjoy!

title: southern peas
directions: Cook onion in butter slowly for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Chop vegetables and place in large bowl.
Add chow mein noodles.
Place remaining ingredients in separate bowl.
Marinate for 1 hour in refrigerator.
Toss all together before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach dip
directions: Run cold water over spinach in colander until thawed.
Drain well on paper towels.
Squeeze all moisture out of spinach.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Stir well. Serve with Town House or wheat crackers.

title: jiffy supper casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion together; put into a casserole dish.
Layer the remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: plain good cake
directions: Stir to combine ingredients in mixing bowl.
Do not beat. Spread batter in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased, unfloured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with sour cream frosting or whipped cream or ice cream.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix well and
roll
in	rolls and then in confectioners sugar.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Spread whipped topping on bottom and sides of a Ready-Crust graham cracker pie crust.
Arrange strawberries, points up, over whipped topping.
Spoon strawberry glaze over berries.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Garnish with additional whipped topping.
Best if served on the same day as made.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour in casserole dish (size depending on how many cans used). Top with
uncooked
bacon strips.	May also add sliced green or red bell pepper strips for color (optional).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until done.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring butter, cocoa, shortening
and 1 cup of water to a boil. Then pour mixture over the flour, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Mix well and add the buttermilk, vanilla and 1 teaspoon salt. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: beef strips oriental
directions: Cut meat into 1/4-inch strips. Place in shallow dish.
Combine ginger, garlic powder, pepper and sugar. Add soy sauce, lemon juice and 1 cup chicken broth; mix well. Pour over meat and marinate 2 to 3 hours.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Mix ingredients except cream.
Fold in 1 cup of heavy cream. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° for 50 minutes.

title: deer fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until brown, then add meat, onions and carrots. Saute until meat is brown.
Add rice, frozen peas and soy sauce and saute for 5 minutes.
Add scrambled eggs.

title: grandma pointelin's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and baking soda and mix. Add flour.
Knead on floured surface until roll and cut consistency.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen medium cookies.
Ice with decorator icing.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add mashed bananas and eggs. Add flour, salt, and soda sifted together, alternately with milk. Stir in nuts and bake in a 8 1/2-inch loaf pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine; add flour.
Add milk and broth.
Add cheese. Boil celery, onion and carrots in water; add this to cheese mixture.
Add mustard.

title: chilies rellenos
directions: Open chilies, rinse and discard seeds.
Put 3 layers of cheeses and chilies.
Beat eggs and combine flour and milk.
Pour over cheeses and chilies.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.
Drizzle tomato sauce over mixture, sprinkle a little cheese, replace in oven until bubbly.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Cut into cube steaks; roll in flour.
Brown lightly in large greased skillet. After browning, place back into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with the soup and 1 can water.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 2 hours.

title: holiday breakfast(this recipe must be made a day ahead)
directions: Ham, sausage or bacon can be added.

title: collards
directions: Wash collards well in several waters.
Remove tough stalks. Put summer collards in with meat, according to their tenderness. Winter collards are put in after meat is tender.
Cook until done. Peeled potatoes or unpeeled "new" potatoes and corn meal dumplings may be added about 30 minutes before collards are done. When done, take up potatoes and dumplings.
Lift collards out of pot liquor.
Drain collards.
Put in bowl and chop with hand chopper or knives until they are cut through well.
Drain again.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, milk, salt and chocolate in a large, heavy saucepan.
Stir mixture over moderate heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil the candy over moderate heat, uncovered, until it reaches 112° to 115° on a candy thermometer.
Remove candy from heat and add butter; cool until lukewarm, about 50°. Do not stir candy while it is cooling.
Add vanilla.
Pour fudge into buttered pan.
Makes 1 pound.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts between wax paper.
Dip in beaten egg, then flour, salt and pepper.
Mix together.
Saute in butter and olive oil until tender, 15 minutes.
Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Arrange broccoli in 9 x 12 baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup butter over broccoli, then grated Parmesan cheese.
Place chicken on top of broccoli, then ham and Mozzarella cheese.
Pour over bouillon cube, mixed with 1/2 cup of water.
Cover and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bahama mama
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender with ice and blend until frozen.
Makes 1 drink.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Use fingers to lightly coat shells of shrimp with oil.
Put shrimp on the grill over hot coals.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Meanwhile, mix the vinegar, sesame oil, salt and pepper in a bowl.
When shrimp are done, remove from grill and toss with mixture in bowl.
Serve hot, letting diners peel and eat their own shrimp.

title: italian meatball sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing lightly, but thoroughly.
Pinch off approximately
1 1/2-inch pieces of beef mixture to make 20 meatballs; place in ungreased 15 x 20-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes or until no longer pink and juices run clear.

title: oyster stew
directions: Clean oysters, reserving liquid.
Heat butter.
Add oysters and liquid and water.
Simmer gently until edges of oysters begin to curl.
Add scalded milk, seasoning and Worcestershire sauce. Garnish each serving with dash of paprika.
If richer stew is desired, substitute 1/2 cup cream for 1/2 cup milk.

title: kielbasa and sauce
directions: Melt margarine; add cut onion and saute.
Add ketchup.
Add kielbasa.
Stir in other ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.
This can be made in a crock-pot.
The longer you simmer it the better the flavor.

title: spicy corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain corn and set aside. In saucepan over low heat, combine cream cheese, butter, milk and seasoned salt. Heat slowly, stirring to prevent sticking. Add corn and peppers. Pour into buttered baking dish. Top with crushed tortilla chips. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: party pate
directions: Fry bacon.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of bacon grease.
Cool bacon and crumble.
Using electric mixer or food processor, beat liverwurst until softened.
Add butter and cream cheese and blend until light and fluffy.
Add parsley, onion, brandy, curry powder, salt and pepper.
I usually omit the salt.
Spoon into crock or serving container.
Swirl top. Cover and chill.
Before serving, sprinkle with crumbled bacon and/or freshly chopped parsley. Serve with assorted crackers and Melba toast.

title: olive salad
directions: Drain, wash and chop the olives.
Chop garlic and celery.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Chop 1 tomato and add before serving.
Serve cold.
Great for picnics.

title: streamlined chimichanga
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain.
Stir in garlic powder, cumin, oregano and picante sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes or until most of liquid has evaporated.
If using margarine, brush one side of tortillas with melted margarine.
Spoon heaping 1/3 cup meat mixture onto center of unbuttered sides.
Fold 2 sides over filling; fold ends down.
Place seam side down in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 475° for about 13 minutes until golden brown.
Top with guacamole and additional picante sauce to serve.

title: cherry treat
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder. Mix until smooth.
Put mixture in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Spoon pie filling into mixture, 4 spoonfuls each direction (16 spots).
Filling will sink into cake while baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until cake tests done.
Cut in 16 pieces while still warm.
Place bottom side up on serving plate.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Add spoon of whipped cream on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Bake in loaf pan (greased) at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until center springs back to touch.
May be 2 loaves, depending on size of loaf pans.

title: french toast
directions: Crack the eggs and put into mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk and mix well.
Add 1 tablespoon of butter in frying pan on low heat (spread butter).
Completely dip each slice of bread in egg and milk mixture, and place in pan.
Cook until both sides are golden brown.
Sprinkle with as much cinnamon as desired.
(Put on syrup, if desired.)
Makes 4 sticks.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars.
Beat egg and vanilla.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in oats. Add raisins and walnuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually stir in pineapple, nuts (1 cup), green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into a ball. Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: key lime cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cake cool in pan on a wire rack.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Cook noodles.
Add sauce and soup.
Mix.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 2-quart casserole until cheese melts, at 350°, for 15 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: In dutch oven or soup kettle over medium low heat, cook onions, sugar and pepper in oil for 20 minutes or until the onions are caramelized, stirring frequently. Add the broth; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Ladle soup into ovenproof bowls. Top each with a slice of french bread and sprinkle with cheese. Broil until cheese is melted. Serve immediately. Serves 8.

title: indian chicken curry
directions: Heat oil in pot.
Add onion; fry until brown.
Add chicken; fry until all liquid is gone.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until tomatoes are soft and chicken is well cooked. Serve over hot white rice.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium bowl.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning in another bowl.
On a large platter, layer as follows:
bean dip, avocado mix, sour cream mix, onions, olives, tomatoes and cheese. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with Doritos or nacho chips.

title: speedy pickled peaches
directions: Drain peach halves; save 1 cup of syrup.
In medium saucepan, combine syrup, sugar, vinegar and cinnamon stick.
Stud each peach half with 3 or 4 cloves.
Add to mixture over medium heat and heat to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with meat, chicken or fish.
(Prepare as before, but use a 29 ounce can of pear halves and syrup instead of peaches.)

title: mystery cake(bake off recipe)
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and oil.
Add the egg and fruit cocktail. Stir together carefully. Put cake mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix together the brown sugar and pecans and put on top of cake dough. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Best served with whipped cream (warm).

title: pie crust
directions: Measure flour and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening and sprinkle in water a tablespoon at a time while mixing until flour is moistened and dough cleans side of bowl.
One to 2 teaspoons water can be added, if needed.
Makes one 10-inch pie crust.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart ungreased casserole, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place casserole in baking pan with about 1-inch hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled, with cream, if desired.

title: nestle toll house cookies supreme
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, butter, vanilla and brown sugar; mix until creamy.
Add salt, baking soda and flour; mix in until blended well.
Add chocolate morsels and stir in well.
Cook 8 to 15 minutes in preheated 375° convection oven for best results.

title: brown bread
directions: Put shortening, molasses and salt in a bowl; pour hot water over it.
Add cold water (if lukewarm).
Add whole wheat flour. Mix.
Add yeast and let dough rest 10 minutes.
Add enough white flour to knead easily.
Knead until elastic.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Drain liquid off tomatoes and pour them into skillet.
Cut tomatoes into pieces and let simmer to lightly boil, adding the sugar slowly.
Tear bread slices into pieces and put into tomatoes.
Let cook 10 minutes after boil on lower temperature.

title: meatballs for pasta
directions: Make small meatballs (18 to 20).
Drop meatballs into boiling sauce; simmer, uncovered, 1/2 hour.
Skim off fat.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk and margarine.
Let cook until thick enough to spread.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Stir and serve over sliced cake.

title: eggplant parmesan(microwave)
directions: Cut eggplant crosswise into 3/4-inch thick slices.
On waxed paper, combine bread crumbs and oregano.
Brush eggplant slices on one side with mayonnaise, then coat on same side with crumb mixture.
In shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole, arrange eggplant slices, crumb sides up, overlapping if necessary.
Cook, covered with waxed paper, on High 12 to 15 minutes, until eggplant is very tender.
Rearrange eggplant slices and rotate dish halfway through cooking.

title: party salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Heat and dissolve Jell-O in it. Add marshmallows and let cool.
When jelled slightly, add the remaining ingredients and fold in Dream Whip.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except last 2.
Bring to boil.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add diced apple.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: cornbread substitute
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Have skillet or skillets hot with plenty of hot oil to keep from sticking. Mix all ingredients well. Pour into hot greased skillet or skillets and cook for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: skillet hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain off fat.
Add other ingredients. Stir.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: banana bread(low-fat)
directions: Mix in order given.
Spoon in greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until done.
Do not overbake.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Combine soup mix and water; boil 7 minutes.
Add rice and simmer 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, saute the sausage and drain.
Add chopped onion, celery and green pepper.
Combine rice and sausage mixture.
Mix well.
Put in casserole and bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's bread
directions: Heat milk until lukewarm; crumble yeast into it.
Add sugar and butter.
Gradually add 1/2 of flour, beating well.
Add salt. Continue adding flour until dough can be handled.
Put rest of flour on kneading board.
Knead dough well.
Place in greased deep pan and let rise at least until double (2 to 3 hours).
Divide dough equally into 3 loaves and place in greased loaf pans for approximately 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake loaves exactly 45 minutes.
Remove from pans and grease all over with margarine or butter.

title: play dough
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently until it balls up.
Remove from heat.
Will keep for days if wrapped in plastic or in a covered container.

title: meat balls
directions: Put ingredients in crock pot on high for 2-3 hours.
Stir frequently.
Sometimes I put the meatballs and wieners together.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat all ingredients
together; pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandmother massey's banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and butter.
Add bananas.
Mix flour and soda.
Add milk, then flour mixture and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Spread broccoli and cauliflower in a baking dish.
Stir together soups, onion, celery and mayonnaise.
(If too thick, add a little milk.)
Pour over broccoli and cauliflower.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash, core and slice tomatoes into thin slices.
In a low bowl, beat eggs, add milk, salt, pepper and flour.
Mix together well.
If too thick, add more milk; if too thin, add more flour. Heat cooking oil in a large skillet.
Dip tomato slices in egg mixture and place in hot oil.
Brown on both sides; serve hot.

title: easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti and drain.
Mix all other ingredients and toss together with spaghetti.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: miracle whip salad dressing
directions: Blend the eggs 30 seconds.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add oil very slowly.

title: old fashion clam pie
directions: Place potatoes, celery, onion and pot herbs in pot. Add water to 1-inch below potatoes.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour mixture into an 8 x 10-inch baking dish, using enough liquid to cover bottom of pan.
Spoon clams with juice over potato mixture.
Place sliced eggs over clams.
Top with crust. Bake at 400° approximately 20 minutes.

title: creamy chicken 'n broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spread stuffing over bottom of greased 9-inch round shallow casserole dish (about 1 3/4-quart). Arrange broccoli spears with flowerets around the outer edge of dish.
Prepare cheese sauce mix according to package directions, using 1 1/4 cups milk.
Stir in sour cream.
Combine chicken and cheese sauce; mix well.
Pour mixture over broccoli stalks.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining onions over chicken; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Bake crescent rolls according to directions.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch mix; spread on crust.
Grate cauliflower, broccoli and carrots and sprinkle on cream cheese mixture.
Chill thoroughly.

title: five bean bake
directions: Mix above ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Heat potatoes, onion, water and instant bouillon to boiling in 2-quart saucepan.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
Place in blender container; add cheese.
Cover and blend on high speed until uniform consistency.
Sprinkle each serving with 1 tablespoon imitation bacon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dandelion gravy
directions: Fry bacon, reserving 1/2 c. grease. Add flour to grease and stir until toasted. Add milk, stirring briskly with a wire whip. Add salt, vinegar, sugar and cheese and stir until mixture comes to a boil. Just before serving, fold in crumbled bacon, eggs and greens. Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Thaw coconut before mixing. Mix bottom 3 ingredients. Set aside while cake is baking.

title: orange-date bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Beat 2 minutes. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, confectioners sugar and butter until it forms a ball. Press on bottom of pizza pan. Bake in oven 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown. Cool.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix lemon jello in boiling water.
Mix cake mix, oil, and eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix lemon extract with cooled jello and add to cake mixture.

title: heaven delight
directions: Mix jello, water, sugar, marshmallows and lemon juice.
Stir well.
Put in refrigerator to thicken.
Add other ingredients when thickened.
Return to icebox.

title: baked potato fries
directions: Place bread crumbs in a shallow dish. Dip fries into egg and dredge in bread crumbs. Place fries in a single layer on an ungreased pan and drizzle with butter. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown, turning once. Sprinkle with salt and serve warm.

title: mushroom steak bake
directions: Combine soup and onion on heavy foil, about 24 x 18-inch. Roll roast in mixture to coat well, then wrap loosely, sealing edges well.
Place on a cookie sheet for easy handling.
Bake in 350° oven for 3 hours.
Remove from oven; reset temperature control to broil.
Slit foil across top and fold back, being careful not to let gravy run out.
Broil roast for 5 minutes, or until top is browned.
Carve into 1/4-inch thick slices; serve it with gravy from foil package.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a bowl; add eggs and buttermilk, stirring until blended.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until set.
Cool on wire rack.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Stir soup and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except chips.
Pour into casserole dish and top with chips.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 45 minutes.
Serve over Chinese noodles.

title: garlic mushrooms
directions: Place margarine, cornstarch and salt in a 1-quart casserole. Add mushrooms and garlic. Cover tightly and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes until hot.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Put ice cream sandwiches in bottom of deep 9 x 13 pan. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Pour some chocolate syrup over the top. Sprinkle Heath Bits on top of chocolate.
Repeat.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and freeze for at least an hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Brown meat, then drain.
Pour meat back into pan.
Simmer meat with tomato sauce 20 minutes.
Add 2 pinches of seasoning.

title: kay frick's overnight tossed salad
directions: Layer vegetables in large bowl.
Cover with salad dressing. Seal to edges of bowl.
Cover with cheese.
Cover salad and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.
(I have added ham and/or chicken, too.)

title: fried chicken breast fillets
directions: Will also need deep fryer and 1 plastic bag.

title: hummus(middle eastern chickpea dip)
directions: Blend garlic, water, lemon juice, oil and salt in blender. Add chickpeas and blend until smooth.
Add tahini and blend; the mixture should have the consistency of thick mayonnaise.
If too thick, add a little water.
Garnish with parsley or mint leaves and serve with wedges of pita bread.

title: stuffed peppers with crawfish or stuffed heads for bisque
directions: Saute onions, celery and 3 medium bell peppers in oleo until very well done, mushy and yellowish.
This takes about 45 minutes. Add crawfish, crawfish fat and seasoning and simmer about five minutes.
Add bread (see directions) and cook about 10 minutes. Fill bell pepper halves and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: great nachos
directions: Cook hamburger meat; drain.
Prepare hamburger meat and taco seasoning mix according to package.
Put Doritos in shallow microwave dish and layer nachos, starting with ground beef.
Top with remaining cheese.
Microwave until hot and cheese is melted. Remove from microwave and top with sour cream.
Enjoy.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle half of pecans into pan. Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Drop in pan.
Melt brown sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Do not boil. Pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle remaining pecans over biscuits. Place in cold oven set at 350°.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Turn onto plate.
Serve hot.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix together and drop on cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: two crust pie pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles grains of rice.
Add water, a little at a time, mixing to a workable dough.
Use more water if needed.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out top and bottom half of crust on a floured board.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugars.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Mix together in a separate bowl the flour, oatmeal that has been powderized in a blender or food processor, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix together all of the above ingredients and add the walnuts, chocolate chips and Hershey bar.
Mix well. Drop on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. These don't last very long around our house.

title: salmon with fettuccine
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Break into large chunks.
Add milk to reserved liquid to measure 1 3/4 cups.
Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until onions are tender.
Add flour.
Cook and stir on low heat until blended.
Remove from heat.
Add milk mixture and wine.
Heat and stir mixture until it comes to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Carefully stir in salmon, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley, dill and pepper.
Season to taste with salt. Cook and stir gently 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve over hot fettuccine.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: If frozen artichokes are used, cook according to directions. Do not overcook.
Drain the artichokes and place them on bottom of a 3-quart casserole dish.
Squeeze as much moisture as possible from the spinach and layer on top of the artichokes in an electric mixer the cream cheese, mayonnaise and butter or oil until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in the milk and spread this mixture over the top of the spinach.
Sprinkle with pepper and the cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes or until the top is lightly browned.

title: pickled squash
directions: Layer squash, onions and pepper. Sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour. Drain and heat other ingredients. Pour over vegetables and bring to a boil. Put in jars and let cool. Chill 24 hours.

title: damali's delicious baked rice
directions: Saute chopped onion in 1/4 cup butter until translucent.
Stir in rice until well coated.
Add the chicken broth.
Cover and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix rice with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Serve at once.

title: cherry glazed pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Rub roast with oil; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place in roasting pan. Roast, basting occasionally with pan juices until meat thermometer inserted into thickest part away from bone register 165°, 50 to 55 minutes. Meanwhile, combine cornstarch with 1 tablespoon water until smooth; set aside. In small pot combine preserves, shallots, bourbon, molasses, soy sauce, ginger, coriander and pepper flakes. Place over high heat; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium; simmer 5 minutes. Stir in reserved cornstarch mixture; cook, stirring until mixture thickens, 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Brush over roast every 5 minutes during last 15 minutes of roasting time. Let stand 10 minutes before carving. Serve with any remaining preserves mixture.

title: scrumptous barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken slowly in oil.
Remove chicken.
Add onions cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Add celery.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes and skim off the excess fat.
Place chicken in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over.
Bake, uncovered, in slow oven (325°) for 1 1/4 hours or until done, basting occasionally.

title: surprise beef and duck soup
directions: Use a wooden spoon to stir.
Add duck beaks, pepper and salt. Stir some more.
Put in a cloth and cook for 6 days.
Stir some more with a wooden spoon.
Add shell noodles and macaroni.
Stir some more.
Add 1 duck's foot; stir some more.
Add eggs and cookies.
Stir some more.
Add water and cake and stir some more. Now you are finished.

title: wild rice-broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Place rice in casserole; arrange broccoli over rice and spread chicken over broccoli.
Combine soup with mushrooms, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over top; cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables or potato chips.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into pie shells. Bake 10 minutes at 400 degrees, lower to 325 degrees and bake until firm. (Cover crust with aluminum foil if it starts to get too brown.)

title: almond tea
directions: Prepare tea with 2 cups water.
Separately boil sugar and peel in 2 cups water for 5 minutes.
Blend tea and sugar mixture.
Add remaining water and remaining ingredients.
Serve over ice.

title: energy candy
directions: Mix above ingredients and roll into balls.
May roll balls in coconut, crushed nuts, raisins, or chocolate chips to decorate.

title: grape-nuts pie
directions: Soak together the Grape-Nuts and warm water. Combine in saucepan the corn syrup, brown sugar and butter. Cook until sugar dissolves. Beat the eggs.
Add part hot mixture, then all and blend. Add the vanilla.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Mix together the flour, oats, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Place small amounts in blender and process until mixture turns into powder.
Mix butter-egg mixture with flour mixture until just blended.
Add chocolate pieces, milk chocolate and chopped nuts.
Roll into balls about the size of golf balls and place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish. Arrange potato slices.
Place browned chops over potatoes. Combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well; pour over chops.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: country ribs
directions: Season ribs with salt and pepper to taste.
Dredge in flour. Heat 2 tablespoons of butter and 2 tablespoons of oil in skillet. Brown half of ribs.
Repeat procedure with remaining butter, oil and ribs.
Reserve pan drippings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients on stove, bring to a boil and boil one full minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats; mix well.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut wings apart at the joints, throw away wing tips.
Heat oil in large heavy skillet over high heat and brown wings lightly, stirring often.
Spread in a single layer in a large baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over wings.
Bake until very tender, turning often.
About 1 hour.

title: pumpkin spice muffins
directions: Grease muffin tin for 12 muffins.
Soak raisins in hot water for 15 minutes.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with sugar, salt and spices.
Gradually beat in pumpkin.
Sift flour with baking powder and soda; gradually add to batter.
Beat in the oil and raisins with liquid.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Ladle batter into tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake muffins for 20 to 30 minutes or until puffed and firm when tested.
Serve warm with butter.

title: peach cobbler pie
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup of boiling water until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup of cold water.
Chill until partially set.
When jello is partially set, fold in the Dream Whip along with the marshmallows and peaches.
Pile into the pie shell and chill thoroughly.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Combine strawberries, pineapple, pecans and marshmallows. Combine remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add to fruit mixture.
Mix well and freeze.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil together to spin a long thread the molasses, sugar and vinegar.
Add
butter and soda.
Add peanuts, if desired. Pour over popped corn; spread over oiled cookie sheet.

title: cheese sausage dip
directions: Melt cheese. Add milk and dressing mix.
Brown sausage; drain. Add to cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: puff pancakes
directions: Set oven to 450° and put a large skillet (cast-iron) or Dutch oven in to heat.
In a bowl, beat the eggs, flour, milk and salt together.
It's important to mix all ingredients together at once, otherwise, your pancakes won't puff.
The more air you beat into the batter, the higher it wil rise in the oven.
When the oven is hot, toss the butter into the skillet and let it melt.
Pour batter into the skillet and return it to the oven.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until the pancake is puffed and golden.
Cut in half and serve immediately with warm maple syrup.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Add oil to iron skillet.
Stir together corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in medium size bowl.
Stir in milk and mix until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: flaskpankaka
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Put under broiler to brown while mixing batter.
Beat eggs, salt and sugar.
Beat in milk and flour alternately.
Pour mixture into hot pan with browned bacon and grease.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with syrup.
Serves 4.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Drain oyster liquid into measuring cup.
Add milk to make 1 cup.
Put cracker crumbs in large bowl.
Add melted butter, oyster liquid, beaten eggs and oysters.
Mix.
Put in greased baking dish and cover with fine crumbs mixed in small amount of melted butter. Bake covered at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Can also be microwaved 7 to 8 minutes, covered, then browned in oven (15 minutes).

title: cheddar apple bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and margarine.
Mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and refrigerate leftovers.

title: grandma sturgeon's squash pie
directions: Mix squash, sugars and eggs together.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Sprinkle some cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Heat and stir the asparagus soup and cream cheese until well mixed.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add flavoring.
Cool and add the asparagus, celery, green pepper, onion, pimento, pecans and mayonnaise.
Stir in the soup-cheese mixture.
Pour into a mold or an 8 x 10-inch glass dish.
Chill until firm.

title: pear salad
directions: Bring pear juice to a boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot juice. Let cool and congeal a little.
Combine cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add this to Jell-O.
Add pears and stir gently. Place in refrigerator to set.

title: philadelphia carrot loaf
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sugar, mixing until well blended.
Blend in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place ingredients in large Pyrex pan in the order listed. Skin chicken breasts and cook in one can of chicken broth.
Add broth to layered casserole.
Place dressing mix on top.
Cook in slow oven, 350°, until hot.

title: spicy beef topped potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; prick well all over with a fork.
Microwave potatoes on High power for 8 to 10 minutes, rotating after about 4 to 5 minutes.
Let stand.
Combine beef and onion; microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir to break up beef; microwave 3 more minutes.
Drain and add picante sauce; cook on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Cut potatoes in halves; fluff pulp.
Sprinkle potato with salt.
Spoon meat mixture on top of potatoes; put a slice of cheese on each potato.
Cover with a foil tent about 2 minutes to allow cheese to melt.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini honey bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and sift together.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to zucchini mixture and stir just until blended. Spoon into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.

title: 3 cheese zucchini casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Layer ingredients. Start with American cheese.
Put Cheddar cheese in middle and end with Swiss cheese. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies - peanut butter cups
directions: Mix crumbs, peanut butter, powdered sugar and melted butter in large bowl.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over crumb mixture.
Refrigerate until cool and cut into squares.

title: creamy seafood enchiladas
directions: In a saucepan on low heat, melt butter; stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually stir in broth and soup; bring to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes.	Remove from heat.
Add sour cream, salsa and salt; set aside.
Place cottage cheese in blender; cover and process until smooth.
Transfer to a bowl; add the shrimp, crab, Monterey cheese, chilies and parsley flakes.
Spread 3/4 cup sauce in a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Place about 1/3 cup seafood mixture down the center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam down over sauce. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with additional salsa.

title: orange tea biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix in shortening with fingertips.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Roll out in a 1/4-inch sheet and spread with an orange filling.
Roll like a jelly roll and cut off in 12-inch slices.
Sprinkle with sugar and grated orange rind over the top.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until lightly browned.
Makes 18 small biscuits.

title: preserved children
directions: Mix children together well and place in field.
Pour brook over pebbles and also place in field.
Sprinkle field liberally with assorted flowers.
Spread deep blue sky over all and bake in a warm to hot sun.
When children are thoroughly browned, remove from field and set in well-filled bathtub to cool.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Mix.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Toss lettuce, tomato, salami and cheese together. Season with dried oregano, basil, salt and pepper, if desired.
Add oil and vinegar to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix everything together in greased dish and top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: olivolis
directions: Cook spinach partly and put through food grinder alternately with slices of French bread and parsley.
Add beaten eggs, cheese, ripe olives, salt and pepper, onion and garlic salt.
Mix well using hands, form a tablespoon of the mixture into cylinders about 1-inch thick and 2-inches long.
Place on wax paper, cover with towel and store in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, bring salted water to a boil in large saucepan.
Drop in olivolis, spacing so they are not crowded.
When done, they will come to the top of the water.
Lift out with a slotted spoon to drain and put them in a shallow casserole or chafing dish to keep warm.
Serve with meat olive sauce.

title: a good simple dessert
directions: Dip some cookies in milk and layer in a round dish.
Spread with cool whip and repeat.
End with cool whip and sprinkle with cookie crumbs.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and melted oleo.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling pineapple juice; add strawberries.
Let set until it begins to jell.
Mix sugar with cream cheese and Cool Whip; pour over pretzels, then pour strawberry mixture over this.

title: turkish pilaf - antoinette pope school - chicago
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt the butter. Add green pepper, tomatoes, garlic, salt, black pepper and mushrooms.
Cook several minutes.
Wash rice 3 or 4 times in cold water and drain thoroughly. Add the washed rice and 2 1/4 cups hot water or stock to cooked mixture.
Stir only until mixed.
Cover tightly.
Let come to a quick boil, then let it cook slowly over low flame about 45 minutes or until tender.
Do not uncover rice while cooking. After rice is done, leave covered about 20 minutes. Delicious served with chicken or any meat dish. Serves 8 to 10.

title: fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine apple and banana with lemon juice.
Add canned fruits and marshmallows.
In saucepan, combine eggs, sugar, cornstarch and fruit juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Toss lightly with fruit.
Fold in whipped topping.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Beat shortening and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Blend in flour mixture. Stir in oatmeal. Chill. Shape dough into balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven. (Take out just before they look done.)

title: fried broccoli
directions: Defrost broccoli.
Heat oil in frypan.
Dip broccoli in flour.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Dip flour-covered broccoli in egg mix.
Follow with bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until browned.
Serve as a side dish with any meat.

title: pineapple fizz
directions: Put into blender. Cover and blend on low speed for 10 seconds or until the mixture is smooth. Pour into 2 tall glasses.
Serve right away.

title: party ham casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese and cook slowly until melted.
Arrange potatoes in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover with green beans.
Pour half the cheese sauce over green beans; add ham and remaining sauce.
Melt remaining butter; mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad (2)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Best if refrigerated 1 to 2 hrs.

title: candy yams
directions: Boil potatoes until they begin to get soft.
Cool.
Peel and slice into patties.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together both sugars, flour and cinnamon.
Melt butter in saucepan and add dry mixture and 1 cup cold water.
Bring to a boil again.
When mixture thickens, add vanilla.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese burger casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper and catsup.
Pour meat mixture into a casserole dish and top with cheese and canned biscuits.
Cook until biscuits are done.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix together water, sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan. Cool until
mixture
thickens.
Remove
from heat and stir in jello. Cool
minutes.
Add
berries
to
mixture and stir. Pour into pie shell.	Chill.	Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots in butter for 10 minutes.
Add flour to mixture, stirring well.
Cook 1 minute.
Combine broth and milk; gradually stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium heat; stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt, pepper and add chopped chicken.
Pour chicken mixture in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Top with pastry; cut slits to allow steam to escape. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: moma mo's punch
directions: Heat sugar, water and salt. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
Mix cranberry juice, lemonade, orange juice, apple juice and pineapple juice; add sugar mixture. Add desired amount of food coloring. Chill for 1 hour.
Add ginger ale before serving. Serve with ice.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: perfect day potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with eggs about 25 minutes or until fork pierces easily; do not overcook.
Drain and refrigerate.
When cold, peel potatoes and cut into uniform small cubes.
Shell and finely chop eggs.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except mayonnaise and sour cream with a fork.
Lastly coat lightly with mayonnaise and sour cream.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla, flour, eggs, chocolate chips and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana pineapple cream pie
directions: Slice bananas in bottom of graham cracker crust.
Mix lemon juice with beaten egg yolks and Eagle Brand milk.
Spread on top of bananas.
Drain pineapple and spread on top of milk mixture. Spread Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, coconut and cherries.

title: ham pate
directions: Place peppercorns in plastic bag.
With a small, heavy skillet or similar heavy object, gently pound peppercorns until coarsely crushed.
In blender or food processor, blend peppercorns, butter, garlic and cinnamon until smooth, about 1 minute.
With motor running, add ham slices, one at a time, and process until minced, about 15 seconds after each addition.
Blend in mayonnaise, mustard and cognac.
Transfer mixture to a tightly covered container. Refrigerate up to 5 days or freeze for up to 3 months.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: beef, beans and noodle skillet
directions: In 10-inch skillet, saute beef until it loses its color.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Saute 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with salt, black pepper, Worcestershire sauce and basil.
Stir in noodles, tomatoes, beans and water.
Add bouillon cube.
Bring to boil; reduce heat; cover and simmer approximately 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until liquid is absorbed.
Makes four servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together and serve with fruit of your choice.

title: smothered teriyaki chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients for marinade.
Marinate chicken overnight.
Preheat gas grill.
Cook chicken with cover down on medium setting 20 minutes, turning once.
Saute mushrooms and onion in margarine and soy sauce until tender in skillet over medium flame.
Spoon sauteed mushrooms and onion over each chicken breast; top with cheese slices.
Cook with cover down 5 additional minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: black forest torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brush sides of bottom of four 9-inch round layer pans with soft margarine.
Bake only 2 layers at a time.
Measure into large mixing bowl, flour, sugar, soda, salt, baking powder, margarine and chocolate.
Add water and vanilla. Beat at low speed to blend, and then beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides and bottom of bowl frequently.
Add eggs; beat 2 more minutes.
Pour 1/4 of batter (about 1 c.) into each pan.
Layers will be thin.	Bake 15 to 18 minutes, or until done. Cool slightly and remove from pan.	Cool thoroughly.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Cover in electric skillet.
Cook 1 hour at 180°.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread cream cheese on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Combine chili with hot pepper sauce.
Spread over cream cheese.
Sprinkle with chili peppers, shredded cheese, olives and onions, in order.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Serve with taco chips and/or vegetables.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: old southern cornbread
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and sugar; mix well.
Add butter, buttermilk and eggs.
Mix well.
Grease an iron skillet with margarine.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: yummy apple cobbler
directions: Mix margarine, egg, flour and sugar together; set aside.
Pare and core apples into a 7 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix apples with lemon juice.
Cut crust from bread and cut into finger-size strips. Place bread on top of apples.
Pour sugar mixture over top of strips.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves six or eight people.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Put bread cubes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sausage on top.
Spread cheese on sausage.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over sausage mixture.
Chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Season meat with Accent tenderizer.
Cook and brown meat and drain.
Saute onion in small amount of meat drippings and drain. Mix onion and meat.
Cook rice per package directions.
Mix soup and milk.
Layer 1/2 of meat and 1/2 of rice and 1/2 of soup. Repeat.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham and corn fritters
directions: Cut butter into 4 chunks.
Bring butter, water, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper to a boil in a saucepan and boil until butter melts.
Remove from heat and stir in flour all at once.
Stir over low heat until smooth and comes away from sides of pan in a ball.
While hot, put in mixing bowl and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in ham, scallion, corn and sage.
Drop by heaping tablespoon into fat and fry until golden, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Calories:
114; fat: 9 gr; cholesterol: 50 mg.

title: fruit salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix sugar with pineapple juice.
Heat; add jello.
Cool; add fruit and refrigerate.
Stir every hour to keep from congealing.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and cut up apples.
Place in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Trim sides off of loaf bread.
Place on top of apples. Mix beaten egg and melted margarine with sugar.
Pour over top of bread slices.
Bake at 350° until brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: devan cream
directions: Put butter and jello in pot and melt slowly.
Put aside to cool.
Put in blender with milk and blend for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Grease bowl and let dough rise as instructed.
Press into greased pizza pan.
Mix tomato sauce, oregano, garlic and oil. Spread on dough.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Add desired toppings and more cheese, if desired.
Bake at 425° until cheese melts and crust is browned lightly.

title: sorbet
directions: Soften ice cream and mix in lemonade and limeade.
Pour in bowl or graham cracker crumb crust and freeze again.

title: carrots
directions: Peel and cut off tops of carrots; slice or dice.
Add water; cover.
Microwave for 9 to 10 minutes.
Add butter; stir and let stand for 2 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix butter, eggs, vanilla and vinegar together.
Add sugar and coconut.
Pour in 2 unbaked 9-inch pie crusts.
Cook at 300° for about an hour or until brown.
Makes 10 servings.
Approximate preparation time: 10 to 15 minutes.

title: topping for cake
directions: Mix all together and boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour over cake while it's hot.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add eggs and butter.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips; add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Let pie cool for several hours. (The last step is very important.)

title: parmesan crostini
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly oil a baking sheet or coat it with nonstick cooking spray.
Place bread slices on baking sheet and brush each slice lightly with olive oil.
Spread each one with about 1 teaspoon Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with black pepper. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until the bread crisps and the cheese is just melted.
Makes 16 crostini; 99 calories each, 1 gram fat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat can of celery soup and add milk and 1/2 stick margarine. Heat until smooth.
Add cheese.
In a large bowl, mix cut broccoli, onion and eggs.
Add the soup mixture; mix until well blended.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onions and slice 3/8-inch thick.
Separate into rings. Pour buttermilk into shallow pan.
Add onion rings and allow to soak 30 minutes.

title: donna's chicken casserole
directions: You will need a 13 x 9 pan.

title: mom's strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until well mixed.
Pour this mixture over the prepared fruit and let stand for 20 minutes. Fill pie shell and then dot with tablespoon of butter.
Put on pastry top and bake for 50 to 60 minutes in a 375° oven.
Be sure to make several cuts in pastry top as pie is very juicy.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix and beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° in greased Bundt pan or 3 greased layer cake pans or 25 cupcakes.
Bake cake 40 to 50 minutes, layers 25 minutes or cupcakes 15 minutes.

title: sherbet ice cream
directions: Finish with milk and put in ice cream freezer.

title: beef barbecue
directions: In roasting pan, cover meat with soup.
Pour barbecue sauce over soup.
Sprinkle dry soup mix and brown sugar over meat. Cover and bake roast in 350° oven for 2 hours or until tender enough to slice.
(For shredded meat, cook about 3 hours or until very tender.)
Drain off fat and remove any bones from the meat. Slice or shred the meat and serve on buns.
Spoon gravy from roast over the meat in the sandwiches.

title: low-fat marinade
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Can be used to marinate poultry, pork, fish or beef.
Grill, bake or broil - whatever!

title: nine day slaw
directions: Grate first 3 ingredients together.
Place the next 5 ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour liquid mixture over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate in a covered container.

title: economical meat loaf
directions: Soften bread in 2/3 cup water in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except bacon.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into 1 or 2 loaves.
Place in baking dish; cut bacon into thirds.
Top loaves with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Shake in mix and store.

title: chili con queso
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put sugar and corn syrup in saucepan; bring to a rolling boil on high heat.
Beat eggs; slowly add hot syrup to eggs, beating constantly.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, then at 300° for 35 minutes.
Use 8-inch pie pan.

title: meal in frypan
directions: Prepare 4 to 6 meat patties.
In a large iron skillet, cook the meat patties for about 15 minutes.
Peel and quarter potatoes and onions.
Dice the bell pepper.
Combine the pepper, onions and potatoes in microwave-safe dish.
Cook on High in microwave for 7 to 8 minutes.
Pour off almost all of the grease in meat.
Add potatoes, onions and bell pepper to meat patties.
Cover and cook all together for about 10 minutes.
Uncover, then brown for about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients
together and roll in chopped nuts. Chill.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter, whipped topping and ice cream.
Stir until blended.
Spoon into crumb crusts. Freeze at least 8 hours. Garnish tops of pies with dollops of additional whipped topping, if desired.
Yields two 9-inch pies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add hamburger meat and brown until done.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Stir in soup and green beans.
Mix.
Mash potatoes according to how you like them.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and place in bottom of baking dish and bake for 15 minutes at 300°.
Then mix together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Mix together puddings and milk and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans on top.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix cottage cheese, spinach and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and eggs.

title: chicken mexicana
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add chicken.
Cook 5 minutes.
Turn chicken over; add green onions and green pepper around edge of skillet.
Cook 5 minutes more or until chicken is tender.
Place rice on serving platter.
Remove chicken and vegetables from skillet and arrange over rice.
Keep warm.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Prepare lasagna noodles as directed. In skillet, brown beef, onion and green pepper; drain. Return beef mixture to skillet. Add corn, salsa and chili powder. In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer 1/3 of meat sauce, 1/2 of lasagna, half the Ricotta cheese and 1 cup Cheddar cheese. Repeat layers, ending with sauce. Sprinkle with olives and remaining sauce. Cover with foil. Bake 30 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. Serve with sour cream.

title: garden dip
directions: In small bowl, stir together yogurt, mayonnaise, red and yellow peppers, celery, shallots and tarragon.
Put in dip serving bowl.
You can refrigerate before serving if you wish.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Debone salmon.
Put in large bowl.
Add egg and bread crumbs (enough so mixture would make a pattie when formed).
Brown in skillet with oil on both sides.
Remove and serve.

title: brandied fruit
directions: Put in glass jar with a stopper lid.
If you use a screw on lid, only set it on.
Do not tighten.
Every 2 weeks, add 1 1/2 cups fruit and 1 cup sugar.
Stir every once in awhile with a wooden spoon.
Do not let fruit go below 3 cups or fermentation will stop.
Great over cake, ice cream or cookies.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Drain.
Combine with sour cream and soup.
Stir in carrots. Spread 1/2 stuffing mix in bottom of a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mix atop.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mashed red skinned potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a medium saucepan with water to cover. Bring to boil over high heat.
Lower heat to a simmer and cook until potatoes are cooked through, about 10 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of the cooking water.
Place the pot over low heat.
Using a potato masher, roughly mash, adding the reserved water, milk, pepper, parsley and butter or oil.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Blend these two ingredients. Knead slightly. Roll; cut and bake. It's a light tasty biscuit. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Beat in heavy cream. Gradually add in flour and flavoring.
Roll out on floured surface 1/8-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with cinnamon, powdered sugar and nuts.
Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Roll up diagonally in small roll.
Put on baking sheet and refrigerate several hours.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: french onion dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: western meal in one
