directions: Brown meat until crumbly; add garlic, salt, onions, green pepper and chili powder.
Saute together; mix in tomatoes, beans and rice.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle olives and cheese over top.
Bake 15 minutes more, then add a little water if it appears dry.
Can use garlic powder instead of clove.

title: press and bake cream cheese crust
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; blend well.
Stir in flour. Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Remove dough from refrigerator and press into bottom and up side of an ungreased 9-inch pie pan or dish.

title: dreams
directions: Crumble together the butter, 1/3 cup brown sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour to an even meal.
Press evenly over the bottoms and slightly up the sides of a lightly buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven until lightly browned.
Mix together 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, eggs, nuts, coconut, 2 tablespoons flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread over baked mixture.
Bake until set. Cool and cut in pieces.

title: one bowl rocky road fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in a 1 1/2-quart microwave bowl on High for 1 minute.
Remove, stir and microwave 1 minute longer. Stir until chocolate is completely melted and smooth.
Stir in vanilla, salt, walnuts and marshmallows.
Spread in greased pan. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: oriental scallops
directions: Place onions and margarine in a 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Microwave, uncovered, at High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir in scallops, orange rind, ginger root, teriyaki sauce and pepper.
Cover with plastic or wax paper.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until scallops are opaque.
Remove scallops and onions with slotted spoon, reserving liquid.

title: lemon fluff(hall of fame)
directions: Chill milk.
Dissolve lemon jello in hot water and chill until partially set.
Whip jello until fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip milk until stiff and then fold together.
Pour into crumb shell and top with some crumbs.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball.
Serve with assortments of crackers.

title: wonderful vegetables
directions: Cook potatoes in pan of water 13 minutes.
Add carrots.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add yellow squash.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add peas.
Cook 2 minutes.
Drain and put in dish.
Add melted butter or margarine. Sprinkle with scallions and parsley, cut up.
Serves 8.
Looks beautiful when served.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together until blended.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crispy fried carrots
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, onion powder, Old Bay seasoning, white pepper, parsley and salt together.
Set aside.
Beat egg white until foamy.
Stir in buttermilk and hot sauce.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix up with garlic powder to taste.
Cook in glass pie plate at 350° for 20 minutes.
To double, cook in a 9-inch plate for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Use your choice of chips.

title: pizza sausage
directions: Brown, crumble and drain sausage.
Put sausage back in skillet and sprinkle with Worcestershire, oregano and garlic salt.
Add 1 pound Velveeta cheese, cut in cubes.
Stir until cheese melts. Put a "dab" (about 1 teaspoon) in the middle of a slice of party rye bread.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Roll into balls the size of a small walnut.
Roll in mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly brown but still soft at 400° approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: no-salt curried squash relish
directions: Grate, grind or finely chop the squash, peppers and onions.
A food processor works well for this step.
In a large saucepan, combine the vegetables, sugar, vinegar and curry powder.
Drop in spice bag.
Bring to boil.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir to remove lumps.
Stir the cornstarch mixture into boiling vegetable mixture.
Cook until the syrup thickens and appears almost clear, about 5 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Pack the relish into clean, hot pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal.
Process in a boiling water bath canner for 10 minutes.
Cool undisturbed for 24 hours.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Dilute mushroom soup with liquid from asparagus or peas, if needed.
In glass casserole, place layer of asparagus.
Cover with soup and cheese, then layer of peas, etc.
Top with layer of cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate philly fudge
directions: Gradually add sugar to softened cream cheese, mixing well until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill several hours. Makes 1 3/4 pounds fudge.

title: favorite french dressing
directions: Mix in blender; if too thick, add 1/2 c. water.
Cook for 1 minute.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 1 qt.
Keeps very well.

title: swiss steak for six
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in flour mixture; brown in oil.
Remove meat to a casserole.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in the skillet from which the meat has been removed.
Make a gravy by adding flour, water and tomato juice to the vegetables.
Pour over meat; bake in a 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and Karo syrup.
Bring mixture to a boil and allow to boil 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir lightly.
Pour over popcorn and nuts.
Mix well.
Place in baking pan.
Allow to bake for 1 hour.
Remember to stir every 15 minutes to keep it mixed well.

title: lasagna for two
directions: Saute beef and garlic in oil in a 10-inch skillet until meat is browned.
Drain off drippings.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Layer half of noodles, Mozzarella, Ricotta, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: grapenut pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk as directed on the boxes.
Fold in the container of Cool Whip.
Stir in Grape-Nuts cereal.
Chill well. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot milk cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed until thick, about 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to batter with vanilla and beat at low speed until smooth.
In a saucepan, heat milk and butter just until the butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Add to batter, beating until combined.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.
Does not need icing.

title: party pizzas
directions: Grate
Cheddar	cheese.
Grate	onion and add to taste. Mix with enough salad dressing to stir easily (approximately 2 to
3 tablespoons).
Drop 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture on top of	party rye
bread.
Place under broiler for a few seconds. Serve warm.

title: martha's shrimp casserole
directions: Mix together; bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake mix per directions on box.
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk on top.
To this, pour small can of crushed pineapple; add juice too.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, 1 1/3 cups instant potato flakes (dry), the egg, salt, pepper, onion, ketchup and milk.
Spread in greased pie pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: artichoke bake
directions: Chop artichokes and mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into egg mixture.
Roll into 1 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge squares
directions: Blend well the syrup, peanut butter, vanilla, butter and salt. Gradually add sugar, making this a very stiff mixture. Knead well, mixing in pecans.
Press into buttered 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: quahaug chowder
directions: Fry salt pork until brown.
Add onions and brown.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup broth and 1 cup water until 3 cups of each have been added.
Add potatoes and cook about 10 minutes.
Add quahaugs and 1 more cup of broth.
Add tomato soup and water.
Let simmer until potatoes are cooked.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage.
Place in large pan with water.
Let cook until almost tender.
Drain water well; salt and pepper to taste. Add soup and mix well.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil the sugar, margarine and evaporated milk together for 8 minutes (rolling boil).
Add the remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Stir until chocolate and Marshmallow Creme are melted and mixture is smooth.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add the nuts.
Pour into pan; refrigerate until cold.

title: butterscotch icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; add baking soda and vanilla. Sift flour and cream of tartar into the creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Roll or shape into a loaf; wrap in waxed paper.
Let stand overnight.

title: yogurt muffins(no fat)
directions: Combine flour, sugar and other dry ingredients.
Gently stir in yogurt, milk and fruit, blending just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups sprayed lightly with Pam 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 18 minutes or until brown.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sierra spinach
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach and drain well.
Chop coarsely.
Combine with all remaining ingredients, except tomatoes, and blend well.
Place in a baking dish and bake for 15 minutes.
Put tomato slices on a baking sheet.
Place in an oven and bake both for 10 minutes longer.
Place a rounded spoonful or an ice cream scoop of spinach mixture on top of each tomato slice to serve 5 to 6.
Preparation time: 15 minutes.
Cooking time: 25 minutes.

title: coconut butterscotch dessert
directions: Toast only 1 cup of coconut on baking sheet at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Stir often until light brown.
Mix flour, butter and walnuts together; add only 3/4 cup walnuts to mix.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apricot dream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
In separate bowl, beat cream cheese fluffy; slowly beat in hot gelatin using mixer. Then beat in pineapple juice (add water, if needed to equal 1 cup).
Chill until slightly congealed.
Add both fruits.
Fold in Cool Whip; fold in marshmallows.
Pour into 9 or 10-inch pan. Decorate with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except beans.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and let simmer for 1 hour.
Stir in beans.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and let simmer as long as you can before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend all together and place in crockpot.
Heat, stirring frequently until cheese melts (about 1/2 hour).

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown meats and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients until melted over low heat.
Spread on party rye bread.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Place in Baggies until ready to use.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach per directions on package.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients (except bread crumbs and margarine).
Top with bread crumbs.
Pour margarine over bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until topping is brown, about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.
Pour into a 13 x 10-inch pan.
Combine crushed pineapple and sugar in boiler; cook for 5 minutes.
When cake is done, use fork to punch holes in the cake.
Pour pineapple-sugar mixture over cake.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on box.
Pour over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rotel meat dip
directions: Mix all together.
Keep warm in crock-pot.
Serve with Mexican chips.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix well.
Serve with fish, hushpuppies, seafood, etc.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Use a small amount of margarine or bacon drippings in a nonstick skillet.
Add shredded cabbage, sliced onion and, if desired, sliced green pepper.
Fry, stirring well, until slightly browned and tender.
Add a little lemon juice and soy sauce.
This goes well with knockwurst, bratwurst or polish sausage.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients except for nuts with mixer until fully smooth.
Form into ball and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. After 2 hours or more, cover with chopped nuts.
Serve with Savory crackers or raw vegetables.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Serves lots!
Smile.

title: scampi(shrimp)
directions: Shell shrimp until last segment, leaving tail on.
With a sharp knife, cut back of shrimp to devein.
Wash and pat dry.
Combine other ingredients, except shrimp, in deep bowl; stir thoroughly until combined.
Taste for seasoning.
Add shrimp; turn them with spoon until totally covered, then cover with plastic foil.
Keep at room temperature for about 2 hours, turning shrimp 2 or 3 times so they are covered and moistened.
Choose a pan you might want to serve in and arrange shrimp in shallow dish just large enough to hold one layer.
Pour marinade over them.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well; chill.
Serve with vegetables and chips.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix together tomato sauce and salt and pepper.
Mix half of this sauce.
Mix with the ground beef, egg, onion and bread crumbs.
Pat mixture into microwave pan and pour rest of sauce on top.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn after 5 minutes.
Let stand covered 5 minutes.

title: greek chicken
directions: Combine first four ingredients in Ziploc bag.
Shake and add chicken.
Marinate 2 hours or longer.
Grill when ready until brown.
Serve with Greek Salad (see "Salads").

title: egg custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and almond extracts. Gradually stir in scalded milk. Pour mixture into chilled, unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Pie is done when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sprinkle on top of cake.
Add 1 cup walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: kids love it eggplant
directions: Brush unheated broiler pan with oil.
Beat together eggs and 2 teaspoons oil.
Dip eggplant in egg mixture; coat with crumbs. Place on greased pan.
Broil 4 inches from heat 2 minutes or until golden; turn.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes more.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Broil 1 minute more until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: squash pot pie
directions: Chop and saute onions and bell pepper; slice zucchini, yellow squash and mushrooms.
Add to onions and bell pepper.
Mix mayonnaise, salt, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese; add to squash mixture.
Line a deep dish pie pan or casserole dish with pie crust.
Place sliced tomatoes over bottom crust.
Pour squash mixture over tomatoes; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Place top pie crust on, seal edges and make slits in top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust is done.

title: hot chili-cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips; heat, over low heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Serve as a dip with corn chips.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Blend drained can of pinto beans in food processor with garlic and lemon juice.
Layer all ingredients in order given in Pyrex dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fried squash
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, salt and pepper.
Dip sliced squash in buttermilk, then roll in corn meal mixture.
Fry in deep fryer until done.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add peanut butter, eggs, vanilla and water.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together. Add to peanut butter mixture.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the soup and sour cream.
Boil chicken until tender (about 1 hour).
Remove from bone unless using boneless chicken breasts.
Tear into pieces.

title: onion zucchini bread
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients (save 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese for top).
Mix together melted butter, buttermilk, eggs and zucchini.
Carefully stir into flour mixture.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch round baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs (1 at a time). Beat thoroughly. Add flour, milk and flavoring. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt margarine; stir in cocoa and add sugar.
Mix well, then add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and nuts; mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream eggs, jam, brown sugar and sour milk together.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and butter. Grease and flour a tube pan or 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add flour and seasonings.
Add milk; cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Add lemon juice.
Remove from heat.
When cool, whisk in egg yolks, then add mayonnaise and shrimp.
Serve over steamed vegetables of choice.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Cream all ingredients together and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers (may be frozen).

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook chicken and pull from bone in chunks.
Arrange broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place chicken over broccoli.
Combine soups, water, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Add extra water or chicken stock, if needed.
Cook 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and add bread crumbs.
Drizzle oleo over top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: red tomato relish
directions: Chop vegetables.
Add salt.
Cook until some of the juice boils down.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook slowly until thick, about 2 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix together cream cheese, Dream Whip and 1 cup sugar.
Spread over crust.
Dissolve jello in 3 cups of hot water.
Drop frozen strawberries into jello.
Pour over cream cheese.
Layer when jello has thickened slightly.
Let stand until firm.
Sprinkle top with crushed pretzels.
Serves 12.

title: bean and cabbage soup
directions: Cook carrot, celery and onion in stock until almost tender, about 12 minutes.
Add beans and cabbage; cook 5 minutes longer. Season.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Prepare or purchase a double pie crust and set one crust in a 9-inch pie plate/pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a soft ball when tried in water (236°).
Add peanuts and cook until mixture is amber colored (294°).
Remove from stove and add salt and soda mixture.
Stir thoroughly and pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: spaghetti pie(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Mix together cooked spaghetti, eggs, melted butter and Parmesan cheese.
Mold into buttered pie plate.
Top with cottage cheese.
Mix browned meat into sauce.
Spread on top of cottage cheese.
Sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix buttermilk and soda; let stand. Cream together margarine, sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Alternately add buttermilk, vanilla and flour.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks and fold in.
Gently stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into 3 prepared round cake tins.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lo-cal lemon-blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and egg whites; beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Add vanilla and lemon; stir.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to mixture alternately with yogurt.
Add berries gently.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased 8-inch or 9-inch loaf pan.

title: cherry nut cookies
directions: Place shortening, vanilla, sugar, egg and water in bowl and beat. Add cherries and nuts. Mix well. Sift together dry ingredients. Gradually add sifted mixture to batter and mix well. Knead dough with hands. Chill dough until firm. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes. Garnish cookies while still warm with a sliver of cherry. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: better "n" fried chicken
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken.
Put pieces in plastic bag with all ingredients and shake to coat.
Place chicken in shallow nonstick baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onion together; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in plate.
Top with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese; bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (8 to 10 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce.

title: coleslaw with ramen noodles
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper together and our over greens.
Add noodles and almonds.
Mix well.

title: 59'ers punch
directions: Combine sugar, cloves, water and cinnamon sticks.
Simmer 10 minutes and strain.
Add orange juice, apple cider and grapefruit juice.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Heat and serve hot.
Yields 3 quarts or 25 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: tim's 5 minute salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and cool whip together.
Stir in jello. Add fruit.
Mix well and chill.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; chill 5 minutes.
Or, for firmer crust, bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half the Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding as directed, using 3 1/2 cups milk; pour over cream cheese layer. Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Garnish with shaved chocolate.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes whole, cool and peel, then dice.
Add the remaining ingredients with enough milk so they aren't stuffy.
Mix together corn flakes and oleo and put on top.
This makes enough for 30 people.

title: spinach rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onions in oil.
Wash and dry mushrooms; slice and fry rapidly in margarine.
Place cooked rice in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Add sauteed onions, some diced green pepper, fried mushrooms and cooked spinach.
Add a little basil, salt and pepper and bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Slice Monterey Jack (10 ounces) and place on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 300°.

title: garden-style oven peas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover with water; cook until vegetables are tender and soft. Turn heat down.
One-half hour before serving, add 1 can evaporated milk.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Mix jello and water together.
Set aside until cool.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill several hours.

title: ginger creams
directions: Blend together sugar, shortening, egg and molasses.
Sift together remaining ingredients except coffee.
Add sifted ingredients to molasses mixture.
Add cold coffee and mix until smooth.
Pour onto large, greased cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Frost with butter icing using cold coffee as liquid.

title: deep fried potato peelings
directions: Peel potato skins thicker than usual.
Wash, dry and then fry in hot oil.
Drain well on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and a heavy coating of Parmesan cheese.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix together butter and cocoa and cool.
Beat eggs and salt. Blend in sugar.
Add cocoa mixture.
Stir in flour and vanilla, mixing well. Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in uncovered roasting pan; do not overlap.
Mix remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes, basting several times.
Serve with wild rice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with oleo. Spread dry cake mix over the top. Stir slightly to partially dampen cake mix. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad(3 layer)
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In large plastic bag, add all ingredients. Close bag and shake well until potatoes are well coated. Place potatoes in shallow baking dish. Bake 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: skillet cheddar cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large mixing bowl;
set aside.
Combine milk, egg and cheese and add to dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into hot, greased 10-inch skillet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until cornbread is golden.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into small balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Reheat before serving if made ahead.
These freeze well.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Mix with mixture of the red wine vinegar, oil and sugar.

title: tuna-chicken casserole
directions: Open the cans and dump everything in a casserole pan, then sprinkle cornflakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Lay chicken and broccoli (odd and even) in casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice in saucepan and heat.
Pour over chicken and top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch oblong pan or same size pie pan.
Heat broccoli to boiling.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix broccoli, onion, pepper and cheese in pan.
Beat other ingredients until smooth.
Pour in pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot supper
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on high about 3 hours.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: dill and shrimp salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the shrimp, lemon juice, lime juice, celery, onion, dill, mayonnaise, and pepper.
Mix well and refrigerate until chilled.

title: spiced applesauce muffins
directions: Grease medium muffin cups or use paper liners.
Beat sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg in a large bowl on medium speed, until light and fluffy.
Beat in applesauce.
Stir in flour, cracker crumbs and spices.
Fold in walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: saucy steak skillet
directions: Fry steak until brown.
Fry onion.
Set aside.
Cook potatoes and carrots for your size of meal.
Save water in which vegetables are cooked.
Put water from vegetables over meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Add potatoes and carrots; simmer until vegetables are almost done.
Add can of green beans.
Simmer until all vegetables are done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Makes 2 small pies or 1 large pie.

title: chocolate crackle cookies
directions: Stir together cake mix, eggs, water and shortening until well blended.
Shape dough into the size of walnuts.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minuets.
They will have a fudge-like center.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: east texas giblet gravy
directions: Chop up meat from heart, gizzard, liver and neck to a medium coarseness.
Heat juice (about 4 cups) from turkey and add 1 cup water mixed with flour, chopped eggs, dressing, salt and pepper. Just bring to a boil to serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In double boiler, put 1 cup sugar, cocoa, 1/3 cup flour, salt, egg yolks, butter and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 30 minutes or until thick.
Remove from fire and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until falls off bone.
Then debone and add peppers, if wanted.
Line bottom of pan with Doritos.
Then layer chicken on top.
Mix cream of chicken and mushroom soups together; thin by adding water.
Pour over the chicken until mixture is moist underneath.
Then sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake about 15 minutes or 20 minutes, until cheese is brown.

title: dilly ham balls(yields 6 servings)
directions: In a bowl, combine ham, bread crumbs, onions, 1 tablespoon fresh dill or 1 teaspoon dried, milk, egg, mustard and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper. Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.

title: pretty christmas cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll in balls and dip in slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in chopped very fine walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press a hole in center with finger and put pineapple or grape jelly in center.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 100 cookies.

title: whipped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover, until tender; drain. Beat potatoes, butter, half and half, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth.
Spread potatoes in buttered baking dish (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch), swirling top with spoon.*

title: tricia's meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll meat mixture into medium balls.
Brown in 1-inch oil until done.

title: country apple cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix with mixer for 5 minutes or beat by hand.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add into oil, eggs and sugar.
Fold in chopped nuts and apples.
Bake in greased, floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Cream shortening; add sugar and cream until light.
Add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients, bananas and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick tests dry.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt margarine.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add sugar. Mix well.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted chips over peanut butter mixture.
Chill for 2 hours.
Cut into 1 to 2-inch squares.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all together and chill well before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: saucy potatoes
directions: Combine and heat to bubbling. Serve hot.

title: torte cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour into two large cake pans and bake.
Cool completely.
Then slice into four layers.
Mix cream cheese, lemon juice and vanilla frosting and spread each of the 3 lower layers with some frosting.
You must leave a large amount for the top layer.
Then over the frosting, spread some cherry filling on each of the lower layers, leaving 1/2 can for the top layer.
Then finish the top layer with frosting and cherry filling.
(I don't do anything to the sides, usually a little juice may run down.)
This is a very good and attractive cake.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Use 3 parts cornbread to 1 part biscuits.
Use enough chicken broth (or turkey broth) to cover.
Beat eggs and stir in.
Add celery and onion.
Add sage to taste.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt. Drain juice from pineapple, reserving the juice.
Add soy sauce and sugar to the juice.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes, basting several times. Place 1 pineapple slice on each breast half.
Baste.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: "easy" sticky buns
directions: Place the frozen rolls evenly in well-greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle the dry pudding over the rolls.
In a saucepan, melt the butter or margarine.
Add the nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well until sugar is completely dissolved.
Pour over rolls.
Cover with waxed paper and a clean cloth.
Allow to rise in a warm, draft-free place overnight.
When ready to bake, preheat oven to 350°. Bake rolls for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan while warm. Enjoy!

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in strips and brown in a little oil.
Add chopped onion and chopped green pepper.
Add 2 cups water, Kitchen Bouquet and salt.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Peel carrots and slice in 1/4-inch segments.
Cook for 20 minutes until just tender and cool.
Slither onions and green pepper.
Add soup, sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and mustard. Mix all together well.
Pour over the carrots.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Stir before serving.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cool milk and add it with egg, salt, sugar, then flour.
Mix and knead.
Let rinse until double in size.
Roll out in circles and brush with melted oleo.
Cut in pie-shaped wedges; roll up.
Brush with oleo again.
Let rise. Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven or until golden brown.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain; set aside.
Saute vegetables in oil until crisp-tender.
Set aside.

title: crispix caramel mix
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Bring to a boil on High in the microwave (2 to 3 minutes).
Boil 2 to 3 minutes longer, stirring several times.
Remove and stir in soda.
Mix well.
Pour over cereal and peanuts in a paper sack.
Put sack in microwave 3 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Spread out to cool on cookie sheet.
Stir often while cooling.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix all together.
Heat until hot. Serve with chips.

title: holiday leftovers casserole
directions: Pan-fry bacon and onion in heavy saucepan until onion is tender, but not brown.
Stir in rice, water, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 15 minutes or until done.
Stir in beans or peas; cover and heat thoroughly.

title: filled nut cups
directions: Mix sweet butter, cream cheese and flour altogether.
Form 24 balls.
Place in small muffin pan and smooth to form a cup.
Beat egg, brown sugar, butter, vanilla and ground nuts well.
Fill cups.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: butter mochi
directions: Mix Mochi and baking powder in a bowl.
Beat eggs and add milk them add Mochi mixture.
Add butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pan.

title: cabbage-stuffed peppers
directions: Remove stems, cut off tops of peppers and remove the seeds without breaking the shells.
Cut cabbage fine as in slaw and add to it the salt and mustard seed.
Mix thoroughly and place in peppers, pressing in tightly.
Place tops on pepper cases and fasten them down with toothpicks.
Place them upright in stone jar* and cover with cold vinegar.
Place cover over jar and put away in cool place until ready to use.
May be kept several months before using.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Mix ingredients and let simmer.
Serve with cheese and sour cream.

title: crunchy refrigerated sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers in cold water, then slice 1/4-inch thick and put in canning jars. Put sliced onions on top.
Mix last 5 ingredients and pour over to fill jars.
Seal and turn jars upside down and put in refrigerator.
Flip jars over daily for 3 weeks. Do not cook.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate in microwave.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan which has been lightly sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be frosted, if desired.

title: freezer dumplings
directions: Heat butter in milk until melted.
Cool.
Stir in egg. Combine with flour.
Roll out and cut.
Lay flat on tray sprayed with vegetable spray.
Place in freezer until frozen.
Put in freezer bags or containers.
To cook, drop in boiling broth over low
heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana nugget cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.

title: cheesy cauliflower
directions: Microwave cauliflower until tender.
Top with mustard mix and shredded cheese.
Cook 1 or 2 more minutes, until cheese is melted. Serve.

title: salad
directions: Cook Soup Mac in enough boiling, salted water to more than cover until water has boiled away, about 30 minutes.
Drain fruits well and save juice.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix well peanut butter, sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Spread melted chocolate chips over this mixture. (You can use large Hershey bars.)
Chill.

title: skipper's linguine
directions: In a skillet cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings in skillet.
Set bacon aside.
Cook onion and garlic in drippings until tender but not brown.
Stir in butter until melted.
Drain cans of clams and tuna.
Break tuna into chunks. Add to skillet along with bacon, olives, parsley and pepper. Heat.
Keep hot.

title: hot turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs, thoroughly.
Place in greased casserole; top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream eggs, shortening and sugars together, blending well. Mix flour, salt, soda and nuts; add to sugar-egg mixture.
Fold in mashed bananas.
Grease and flour a bread pan (large size) and pour in mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: ham and broccoli quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese, onion, ham and broccoli in bottom of pie crust.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over ingredients in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce oven to 300° and finish baking until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: green tomato filling cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in slow oven at 275° to 300° approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick or tester comes out clean.

title: harvey house griddle cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar together.
Add eggs, margarine and milk to flour mixture; beat well.
Spoon onto hot griddle and cook until done on both sides.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, saute celery and onion in oil for about 1 to 2 minutes or until tender.
Do not brown them.
Add the potatoes, water, butter, salt and black pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-high and cook until the potatoes are fork-tender, not mushy.

title: stuffing patties
directions: Saute onions, celery leaves and sausage until well done.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Scoop into small balls and refrigerate overnight.
Flatten balls and brown in oleo until done.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Wash broccoli, green onions and cut stems and tops.
Saute broccoli and onions in butter, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes.
Add potatoes and chicken broth and bring to a boil. Cook about 20 minutes.
Thicken the milk with cornstarch, stirring with wire whisk until smooth.
Add to first mixture and cook slowly for a few minutes.
Serve with shredded cheese on top.

title: crisp nut cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk until creamy. Add flour and vanilla. Spread mixture very thinly with spatula onto lightly greased 10 1/2 x 16-inch cookie sheet. Cover batter with beaten egg white. Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Press pecans into the batter with hands or spatula. Bake at 325° until lightly browned or firmly set. Cut while hot by pressing spatula lengthwise to make squares. Remove with spatula just before crisping.

title: crybaby cookies
directions: Cream the shortening. Beat in sugar, molasses and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and mix with coconut, nuts and raisins. Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Drop teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 9 1/2 dozen.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and oil; add eggs, flour and bananas.
Mix well; add soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: gazpacho delight(serves 10)
directions: A food processor makes this recipe a breeze.
But even if you chop the vegetables yourself, you'll have this salad prepared in almost no time.
Gazpacho is traditionally served uncooked, but it needs to sit for several hours to allow flavors to permeate.

title: taco filled peppers
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, beans (rinsed and drained) and salsa.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cut peppers from top to bottom. Remove seeds and stems.
Immerse peppers in boiling water for 3 minutes; drain.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into each pepper shell.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with tomato, cheese and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavorings.
Continue beating until well mixed.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add to buttermilk. Then add buttermilk and yeast to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Cut biscuits after you have rolled out dough.
Dip in melted butter and place on greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: baked scallops
directions: Butter the inside bottom of casserole dish.
Add scallops, then pour wine over scallops.
Pour half the butter over them. Cover with bread crumbs, then cover crumbs with remaining butter. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: teresa's holiday cranberry sauce
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar in water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil.
Add cranberries and return to boil. Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until cranberries "pop".

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine sugar, jello and hot water, then add other ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Take crescent rolls and spread on pizza pan or baking stone with points to the middle; mold crescents together to make a crust. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Remove and let completely cool.

title: lite peach cheesecake
directions: In blender, sprinkle gelatine over water; let stand 2 minutes. In a small saucepan, bring reserved peach juice to a boil.
Add juice to blender and process at low until gelatine is completely dissolved (2 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients and process at high until blended.
Pour into an 8 x 9-inch pie pan or crust prepared with 3/4 cup graham cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Garnish with peaches.

title: chuck hutzler's crab salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and chill before serving.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: candy peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and butter in heavy 4-quart pan.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Put in a candy thermometer, continue cooking without stirring to 280°.
Then stir in nuts gradually, stir occasionally and watch closely until mixture reaches 300°.
Remove from heat and add soda gently, but quickly, stirring all in at once.
Pour on 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Do not spread!
Cool and break.

title: asparagus and shrimp casserole
directions: *Broccoli may be used as a substitution.

title: peanut butter honeys
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheet. Sift together and set aside the flour and baking soda. Cream the peanut butter, butter and vanilla. Add gradually, creaming until fluffy the sugar and honey. Add dry ingredients, 1/4 at a time.
Mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoon onto greased sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chewy pralines
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and salt
to
245° or hard boil.
Add oleo, milk and nuts slowly.
Try
not to stop boil.
Cook over medium heat to 245°,
stirring constantly (mixture will stick) about 25 minutes.
Add 1/2
teaspoon vanilla.
Let stand a few minutes. Beat and drop
on
buttered
platter.
Cool
at room temperature. Makes about 30 (2-inch) pralines.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Combine juices in punch bowl.
Add scoops of sherbet; pour ginger ale over this.
Makes 25 (6 ounce) servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add soda, salt and spices; sift together 3 times.
Cream shortening; add sugar, gradually beating thoroughly after each addition until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and prunes and beat until well blended.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time (about 1/3 at a time), beating after each addition.
Turn into two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Frost with boiled frosting or Mocha Frosting.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Combine all marinade ingredients.
Add chicken and coat all pieces.
Cover, seal and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Grill on barbecue grill until tender and done or bake for 30 minutes at 350° until tender and done.

title: denver omelet
directions: In a bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.
Add water; continue beating about 1 1/2 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Fold yolks into whites.
In an ovenproof skillet, heat margarine until it sizzles.
Pour in egg mixture, mounding it slightly higher at the sides.
Cook over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until puffed, set, and golden brown on the bottom.
Then bake in a 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center
comes out clean.
Loosen sides with a metal spatula.

title: cheese topped vegetable bake
directions: Cook carrots and green beans until tender and drain.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
In skillet, melt margarine.
Add onions, basil, garlic salt, pepper and mushrooms; saute until onion is tender.
Spoon onion mixture over carrots and green beans; top with tomato wedges.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix strawberries and jello with white cake mix. Then add water and wesson oil and strawberries and eggs. Beat real good and bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolk and mash yolk with fork.
Combine with remaining ingredients; blend well.
Refill egg whites using approximately 2 teaspoons mixture per egg half.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and eggs well.
Mix flour and sugar.
Blend dry ingredients while adding small amounts of creamed Crisco and eggs; blend well.
Add vanilla flavoring and stir.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan for 20 minutes, then remove onto plate.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans in cold water overnight.
Drain beans; add hot water and sliced vegetables.
Add meat and spices.
Cover; simmer slowly 1 1/2 hours.
Melt butter; stir in 1 tablespoon flour and several dashes of paprika.
Add some broth from soup to make paste.
Stir this back into soup and cook a few more minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix.
Heat oil in skillet. Drop 1/4 cup of batter into skillet for each pancake.
Brown on one side, turn, and brown on other side.
Remove with spatula to warm plate covered with paper toweling.

title: corn spoon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 8-inch or 9-inch pan. Top with 1 1/2 cups of grated Swiss cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
You may double recipe and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well. Slowly add sugar. Add condensed milk and then Pet milk. Add vanilla. Beat until well blended. Pour into ice cream freezer. Fill the rest of the way with whole milk (up to 2-inches from top). Freeze.

title: chicken in french onion sauce
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In an 8 x 10-inch baking dish, combine wine, bouillon, garlic salt and pepper; pour over chicken and veggies.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes. Baste chicken with wine sauce and top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes.

title: white sugar cookies(mrs. lavina hackney's)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use enough flour to make dough soft. Roll out and cut with cutters.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: chili sauce for hot dogs
directions: Saute ground beef and onion together until meat is brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: peach streusel pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and butter or margarine.
Put half of mixture in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, nutmeg and sliced peaches and pour into shell.
Beat egg and milk and pour over peaches.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Cover edges of shell with foil to keep from overbrowning.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into
a 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Let cool before cutting.

title: judi's beef stroganoff
directions: Heat cooking oil in a large pot or frying pan and brown beef in it.
When meat is browned, add Worcestershire sauce, ketchup-water, garlic powder, bay leaf, salt, allspice and wine.
If you wish, add liquid from can of sliced mushrooms at this time.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add cream of mushroom soup (do not dilute) and sliced mushrooms.
Heat through.
Add remaining 1/4 stick butter and heat through.
Add sour cream.

title: bean salad
directions: Let stand 24 hours.
Pour off excess dressing before serving. May be served plain or on lettuce.

title: fish mold
directions: Heat soup to quick boil.
Add softened gelatin; mix and dissolve.
Add softened cream cheese; beat well.
Add mayonnaise; blend well.
Add celery, onion and tuna or crab.
Mold and chill.

title: cheesy mexican dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine sour cream, milk and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in chicken, cumin, salt, green chiles and hot sauce.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Arrange chopped tomato around outer edge of chicken mixture, place reserved chiles in center.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend onion, bell pepper and nuts, using some of pineapple juice in blender.
Combine all ingredients.
Roll ball in chopped nuts.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix with undrained pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Add walnuts, if desired.
Mix well and chill. Can be frozen.

title: canape bases and spreads
directions: Mix together.
Spread on toasted bread.
Broil quickly and carefully (cooks fast).
Serve hot.

title: banana pudding or cherry
directions: Combine milk and pudding.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Mix until smooth.
Layer in a container cookies, bananas or cherries and the pudding mixture.
This makes a large pudding.
A little crushed pineapple (drained) can be added to the banana pudding (optional).

title: vernell's fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Mix flour and Old Bay seasoning in paper
bag.
Heat cooking oil in large skillet.
Combine water and egg in mixing bowl.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in flour mixture (a
few
pieces
at
a time).
Fry over medium heat until golden brown, about 20 minutes on each side.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Combine eggs, soup, cheese and mayo.
Fold in broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with crackers and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: casserole staliano
directions: In a skillet, brown beef with onion and seasonings.
Stir until well combined.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine hamburger mixture with soup and water.
Add noodles.	Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve over ice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place biscuits on cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Open biscuits on cookie sheet.
Mix with mixer until blended well sour cream, cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread on top of a biscuit, then sprinkle carrots, cauliflower, broccoli and cheese on top.

title: light continental chicken
directions: Saute chicken, mushrooms and garlic in oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except rice, and bring to a full boil. Stir in rice, remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes. Makes 4 servings; 350 calories per serving.

title: quick quiche lorraine
directions: Combine all and pour into baked pie shell. Bake at 300° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon butter
directions: Allspice:
pot roasts, squash, fish, eggs, sweet potatoes.

title: cheddar sausage muffins
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet until cooked thoroughly, breaking into small pieces; drain.
In a bowl, combine soup, cheese and water.
Add biscuit mix and stir until well blended.
Add sausage. Place batter into greased muffin cups, filling about 3/4 full.

title: glazed sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange in greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: baked russian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line shallow pan with foil wrap.
Place chicken in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 45 minutes, then uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Top with one 12 ounce bag of chocolate chips. Return to oven until chips have melted enough to spread evenly over cookie mixture. Cut into squares and serve when cool.

title: amanda's creme brulee
directions: Preheat oven to 400. In a large bowl whisk together egg yolks and sugar until sugar has dissolved and the mixture is thick and pale yellow.

title: green pepper hamburger casserole
directions: Precook peppers in boiling water 5 minutes. Brown meat and onion. Add corn, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and monosodium glutamate.
Simmer until heated through (5 minutes). Add cheese. Stir until melted.
Layer meat, pepper strips, meat, etc., in baking dish. Top with buttered crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Cook 2 minutes over low heat.
Add milk. Bring to boil. Cool.
Add confectioners sugar and mix well.
Immediately spread on cooled cake.
Yields enough for one 2 layer cake.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour, vanilla, salt, nuts and apples.
Add soda last.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put in saucepan the clear jell, sugar, salt, Karo syrup and coloring; stir together and add the cold water.
Then add hot water and place on stove to boiling point for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and add the jello.
Stir until dissolved and let cool until just cold, then add washed, drained and cut strawberries. Fill the pie crust and refrigerate until it thickens.
Top with whipped cream or Rich's topping.
Delicious!

title: chicken wing dings
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over wings in shallow Pyrex. (Mixture should cover wings.)
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Cook in same container with foil covering at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and turn wings.
Leave uncovered and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: seafood sauce & seafood cream cheese ball
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and refrigerate to chill.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and form into a ball.
Chill the cheese ball for 3 hours.
When ready to serve, pour the sauce over the cheese ball and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water; add pineapple juice.
Chill. Pour over ice in punch bowl; add chilled ginger ale.
Serve at once.
Pour over 2 or 3 pints sherbet for an extra special punch. Use raspberry sherbet with red punch and pineapple or lemon sherbet with green punch.
Yield: 50 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Separate egg whites.
Blend flour, sugar and 1/2 can of milk. Add egg yolks; beat.
Add remaining milk, water and vanilla; blend. Cook on medium-high heat until mixture gets hot, then lower temperature to medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add butter when mixture is hot.
Cook until desired thickness is reached.

title: impossible pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate. Mix ingredients in blender for 1 minute. Pour into greased pie plate. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: breast of chicken on rice
directions: Mix soup with milk; save 1/2 cup of mixture.
Mix remaining soup mixture with rice, mushrooms (including liquid) and half of onion soup mix.
Pour into casserole dish.
Place breasts on top. Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine in large bowl.
Stir and set aside.
Mix dressing in separate bowl.

title: ring salad
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add rings and cook until medium.
Mix with all ingredients and refrigerate.
Season to taste.
Recipe may be halved.

title: hamburg pot pie
directions: Pour into an unbaked pie shell on 9-inch plate; cover with top crust.
Make slits for steam.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in shortening in a skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, adding more tomato juice, if necessary.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Makes 6 to 8 Sloppy Joes.

title: cereal snack mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large plastic bag; set aside. Combine butter and remaining ingredients; cool slightly and pour into bag.
Close and shake until well coated.
Divide mixture into 2 large roasting pans; place pans on oven racks, one above the other, in same oven.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight containers.
Yield:
8 quarts.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Makes 2 servings.

title: bowl dessert(looks very good in punch bowl)
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, stir until slightly thick.
Mix pudding as directed. Cut cake in bite size chinks, make layer in bowl.
Pour jello on cake and then pour pudding.
Make 2 more layers and top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Can then top with chocolate, cherries or bananas, or all 3.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients in order listed and beat until smooth.
Cook on griddle at 325°.
Makes 20 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Drain beans well; add vinegar and heat to boiling.
Add sugar and
pimentos.
Crush
bacon
into	bits.
Just
before serving, for crispness add onion and bacon bits.

title: deer camp pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo, add bouillon cubes, water, noodles and broccoli.
Cook until tender.
Add milk, cheese and garlic salt. Cook slowly until cheese is melted.

title: little smokie potato cheese soup
directions: Put smokies, celery and onions in a pan; cook until tender. Drain off grease.
Mix in potatoes.
Cover with water; cook until tender, not mushy.
Drain water.
In other saucepan, mix soup, celery, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Cook until cheese melts.
Dump with other ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sour cream enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Add onion and green pepper. Continue cooking until onion and pepper are soft.
Add next 8 ingredients. Simmer 5 minutes more.
In microwave, melt margarine. Add flour. Stir in
milk. Microwave on High 6 minutes, stirring well every 2 minutes. Blend in sour cream.
Heat 1 minute longer, but do not boil.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch casserole. Cut tortillas into 6 to 8 wedges each and line casserole with half of the tortilla pieces. Top with meat mixture, sauce and grated cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 25 minutes until sauce is bubbling.

title: rice and hamburger
directions: Put oil in pan; pour in rice and brown. Add onion and hamburger meat. Cook real done; salt to taste. Add tomatoes. Cover and cook 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: holiday-golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; cut into squares.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes and shake a few at a time in bag, coating well with cheese mixture.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan; place potatoes in layer and bake at 375°
for 1 hour, turning once during baking.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stew meat special
directions: Put meat, onions, consomme and soup in electric casserole, such as a crock-pot, on low.
Cook 8 hours or so.
Serve over noodles.

title: brownulated cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon, then gradually add to sugar and butter mixture until well blended.
Roll out on floured surface and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Glaze lightly with mixture of confectioners sugar and water.
Enjoy!

title: old time beef stew
directions: It is the browning that gives a stew the rich color and flavor everyone likes.
Heat oil in Dutch oven; add beef cubes and brown on all sides.
Turn cubes with tongs and add slices of onion, along with garlic, boiling water, salt, lemon juice, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, paprika, bay leaves and allspice or cloves.
Gentle cooking is what makes the meat tender.
Cover and simmer (not a boil) 2 hours.
Stir now and then to prevent sticking.
When meat is almost done, add the vegetables.
For handsome looks, cut each kind of vegetable the same size.
Now simmer the stew until everything in the kettle is tender.
Discard bay leaf and garlic cloves.

title: tortellini and spinach
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix creamed spinach with milk in bowl. Spoon half the creamed spinach mixture into shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with half the tortellini and chopped tomatoes. Repeat layers with remaining creamed spinach, tortellini and tomatoes. Sprinkle with basil and Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered with foil, for 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spiedano romano buns(ham-swiss cheese)
directions: Cream the butter, onion, mustard and seed.
Spread on each side of buns.
Place slice of ham on bottom half of bun.
Cover with a slice of cheese.
Top with remaining half of bun.
Spread top of bun with butter mixture.
Cook 3 sandwiches at a time for 2 minutes and 30 seconds.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan. While warm, pick with fork and add 1 can milk over top.
When cake is cool, add 1 package of thawed coconut to Cool Whip and ice.
Add second thawed package of coconut to top of icing.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain. Add all other ingredients. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for approximately 35 minutes. Makes 17 cups.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, stir together sugar, milk and salt. Mix well.
Add peanut butter and cover.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Stir well.
Microwave at Medium for 10 to 14 minutes, uncovered.
Stir well every 5 minutes.
When sufficiently cooked a few drops of mixture will form a soft ball in cold water (candy thermometer will read 235°).
Let candy stand without stirring at room temperature until lukewarm.
Add vanilla. Beat with spoon until thick and it loses its gloss.
Quickly stir in the nuts and pour into an 8 x 4 x 3-inch buttered loaf pan.
Cut when set.
Makes 1 pound.

title: margarita
directions: Stir well with 3/4 cup cracked ice.
Pour into glasses, the rims of which have been rubbed with citrus rind and then spun in salt.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add oil slowly and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and soda; stir into creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a prepared 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant au gratin
directions: Pare, dice and cook eggplant in boiling water until tender. Drain well and mash.
Add egg and mix well.
Layer in greased baking dish, eggplant sprinkled with cheese, salt and pepper, cayenne pepper and dot with butter.
Repeat process with cheese layer on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave cod fillets
directions: In glass baking pan, slice onion and put in bottom of baking pan.
Slice 1/2 stick of butter in thin slices; place over onions in bottom of baking dish.
Put in cod fillets so they are lying flat.
Sprinkle lemon juice on top of fillets.
Cover with microwave wrap; vent one of the corners to release the steam. Bake on High for 7 minutes if frozen or 4 to 4 1/2 minutes if thawed.
Take out of microwave; turn fillets over and bake on High for 7 minutes if fillet was frozen or 4 to 4 1/2 minutes if fillet was thawed.
Cover again with microwave wrap.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Stir in Cool Whip. Line pan with graham crackers in bottom of pan.
Then pour pudding mix over them.
Repeat layers.
Finish with crackers on top.
Ice top.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: soy sauce steak
directions: Slice steak into very thin slices and set aside to soak in 1/2 bottle of soy sauce and flour for about 30 minutes.
Set your electric skillet on high using no oil.
Stir-fry steak until tender.
Add mushrooms, onions and peppers and let cook down a little, then add about 4 cups of water and a bottle of the lite soy sauce.
Cover and let the vegetables get tender.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves about 6 to 8 people.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Let cucumbers stand in lime water for 24 hours; drain.
Soak in cold water for 4 hours, changing water each hour.
Bring sugar to boil.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Bring all to boiling point and seal in jars.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook rice according to package; set aside.
In 3-quart pan cook onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sausage and Creole seasoning.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in chicken pieces and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes or until chicken is done.
Stir in cooked rice; serve with okra.

title: herb-ox soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients combined for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange eggnog
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler. Beat egg yolks with sugar. Stir in about 1 cup hot milk. Quickly stir into remaining hot milk in double boiler and cook, stirring constantly over simmering water until mixture thickens and coats a metal spoon. Remove from hot water and add vanilla. Chill. Add undiluted orange concentrate. Makes
16 1/2-cup servings.

title: beef fajitas
directions: Cut beef into strips and set aside.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over high heat; add meat and stir-fry until browned. Transfer meat to a bowl.

title: perky punch
directions: Pour juices and water into an electric percolator.
Add brown sugar.
Place cloves and cinnamon in the percolator basket.
Perk through complete cycle; serve hot.
This can be heated for a while in a pan on the stove if you don't have a percolator.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt, cinnamon and soda; sift over fruit and pecans,
mix
well.
Cream
oleo
and sugar; add to fruit mixture. Beat
eggs
well,
pour
over
fruit mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard. Set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine eggs, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper. Add 1/2 cup of tomato sauce mixture and stir thoroughly. Place meat mixture in glass ring mold or 2-quart microproof round casserole. Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat. Cover loosely and cook on HIGH 12 to 14 minutes. Let stand, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water.
Add rest of ingredients and spread on cookie sheet and bake.

title: pumpernickel bread dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill overnight.
Serve with 1 pound pumpernickel bread.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn; set aside.
In saucepan, cook sugar and butter until sugar is dissolved.
Add marshmallows.
Stir constantly until marshmallows are melted and well blended.
Pour over popcorn; form into balls or leave in bowl.
(Popcorn will remain chewy and soft.)

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples and vanilla pudding together.
Beat egg yolks, sugar, cream, melted butter and lemon together.
Beat egg white until stiff; mix ingredients together.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked onion
directions: Peel off outer skin and wash.
In a greased casserole, place the onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour a can of cream of mushroom soup over onions (1 can for 6 onions).
Cover each onion with 1/4 cup of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until fork can pierce onions easily, about 30 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter; saute carrots and onions.
Add broth.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Stir in 4 tablespoons flour.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine roux and broth.
Add cheese and parsley. Stir well.
Season to taste.
Top with green onions when served.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, melted oleo and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: kraut
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 40 to 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of the beans in a casserole.
Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add chestnuts.
Spread with 1 can of soup on top. Add second layer of green beans; sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cover with 1 can mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle French fried onions on top.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fill loaf pans 3/4 full which have been greased.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: zucchini-beef casserole
directions: Arrange squash in greased 2-quart casserole.
Add onion and green pepper.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with crumbs. Pour undiluted soup over all.
Sprinkle or layer with cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Brown ground beef; season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 25 minutes longer.

title: english breakfast
directions: In a large skillet with a cover, cook bacon slices over moderate heat until they are crisp.
Transfer the bacon to paper towels to drain and keep warm.

Pour off all but 4 tablespoons of the fat from the skillet; add plum tomatoes and cook over moderate heat, stirring the mixture to break up the tomatoes, for 5 minutes. Add sugar, salt and pepper to taste and cook the mixture until it is thick.
Pour off 1/2 to second skillet.

Gently break 8 eggs over the mixture in each skillet; sprinkle them with salt and pepper to taste and cook the mixture, covered, for minutes or until the eggs are cooked to the desired degree of doneness.
Divide the buttered toast among 8 heated serving plates, arranging them on one side of each plate.
Transfer 2 eggs with a spatula to the opposite side of the plate; spoon the tomato mixture over them and put 2 slices of bacon on each slice of toast.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together honey, oil, pumpkin, chopped dates, walnuts, salt, cinnamon, cloves and baking soda.
Add flours and wheat germ.
Spray loaf pans.
Bake for one hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Drain sweet potatoes and place in casserole dish or mash partially.
Add the rest of the ingredients and continue to mash all together.

title: mocha cheese cake
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler or microwave. In a small mixing bowl, beat cream at a very high speed until soft peaks form; set aside.

title: tasty tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes, then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a jelly roll pan 15 minutes at 350°.
While hot, spread with peanut butter, about 4 to 5 tablespoons.
Refrigerate until cool.
Spread melted chocolate, either 2 large Hershey bars or one 12 ounce bag of Hershey's chips (milk chocolate).
Let harden, then cut into squares.

title: baked ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, beef, pork, bread crumbs, egg and tomato puree. Form into a loaf pan.
Steam for 1 hour and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with tomato sauce or grilled pineapple slices. Makes 16 portions.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Empty beets and their liquid into a small saucepan.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt; heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Place eggs in a preserving jar.
Pour in beet mixture and add just enough of the water to cover eggs. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks before serving, stirring occasionally.

title: sarah's tea cakes
directions: Mix with your hands!
Mix margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, mix well.
Add flour until the dough is stiff enough to handle.
Roll out as thin as pie crust if you want really thin cookies or about 1/2 inch thick for thicker cookies.
Cut with any cookie cutter you prefer.
Bake at 400° until the edges are light brown.
If you roll them thin, you will have a lot of cookies.

title: snow bread
directions: Mix and bake 40 minutes in hot oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix the eggs, mayonnaise and soup, then add the cooked, well drained broccoli.
Put in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: seafood surprise
directions: Saute butter or margarine in large skillet with onion and green pepper.
Add crab or lobster meat; cook for 10 minutes.
Add can of mushroom soup; cover and let simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice; season to taste.
Serves 4.

title: frozen meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet so they don't touch.
Freeze until hard, 3 hours or longer.
Quickly remove frozen meatballs and store in a plastic container or bag.
When ready to use, place frozen meatballs in oil and brown all over.
Transfer to crock-pot and cook with barbecue sauce (one bottle of Ken Davis is best) for 2 hours.

title: peach custard ice cream
directions: Heat milk and cream together with vanilla bean in heavy pan over low heat. In large bowl, mix eggs, sugar, flour and salt and stir in a little of heated milk-cream mixture. Pour contents of the bowl into the heavy pan with remaining milk-cream mixture. Stir over low heat, without scorching, until thick and smooth. Remove from heat; discard vanilla bean and add peaches. Place in hand-cranked churn or electric ice cream maker and churn until cold and thick. Let mellow 30 minutes in freezer before serving.

title: vegetable samosa
directions: In a saucepan, boil potatoes in salted water 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well, return to saucepan and shake over low heat a few moments or until dry.
Mash well.
Cook peas in boiling salted water 4 minutes.
Drain well.

title: toffee torte
directions: Mix together by hand.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and press in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook sugar, water and cranberries until berries start to pop. Add Jell-O and marshmallows to warm mix.
Cool, then add other ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: floating taco
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Simmer with remaining ingredients for 2 hours in crock-pot on low.
Starting with taco chips, pour sauce over the chips and top with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese. Other ingredients could include sour cream, black olives, jalapeno peppers, salsa, etc.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla, then add Rice Krispies.
In a double broiler, melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth.
Leave over low heat.
While this is melting make the peanut butter balls to desired size.
Dip in chocolate and drop on wax paper.
They are set up in 10 or 15 minutes.

title: polish honey cookies
directions: Combine honey and sugar. Add eggs; beat. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger. Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Shape into a ball and refrigerate 2 hours. Roll out on a floured board to a 1/4-inch thickness and cut with a round cookie cutter. Brush top of each cookie with egg white and press an almond into the center. Cook on greased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: steak and kidney pie
directions: Cut steak and kidney into bite size pieces; put in a bag with flour and toss until well coated.
Melt drippings in a saucepan; add meat and onion.
Fry until brown.
Stir in stock and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in mushrooms and allow 30 minutes for cooking. Put in dish to cool.
Put pastry over mixture.
Bake in a 425° oven.

title: ice pops from fruit juice(kids)
directions: Take your child's favorite juice.
Pour into ice cube trays and freeze.
To serve, pop into small plastic bag.
Use plastic bag to catch the drips.
To make a popsicle type, put sticks in trays covered with Saran Wrap.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Add chopped nuts.
Grease and flour 1 tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: marinated vegetable salad
