directions: Bring to boil sugar and vinegar, stirring to dissolve sugar. Let cool.
Combine remaining ingredients with vinegar mixture. Cover and chill, stirring ingredients several times.
Chill at least 8 hours.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Cook beans and then mash pinto beans.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix together sugar, flour and baking powder.
Then mix the 2 together.
Pour into unbaked but dry out in oven pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: maple bran muffins
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center.
Combine egg and maple syrup in small bowl, stirring well; add bran flakes and let stand 5 minutes.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yield: 15 muffins.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve the first 8 ingredients, then add the ginger ale and congeal.
Later add celery, grapes, pineapple and nuts.

title: great ham rolls(appetizer)
directions: Spread thinly sliced ham with 1/4 inch of cream cheese.
Take 1 whole green onion, washed, dried and ready to eat and hold it lengthwise of ham.
Trim
onion to fit ham and roll up the onion lengthwise in ham to form a ham roll.
Make as many as you wish; refrigerate until ready to serve.
Cut ham rolls in about 1/2 to 1-inch pieces.
One ham roll equals about 8 pieces.
Refrigerated ham rolls last up to 1 week if wrapped in foil.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain and rinse in cold water. Place in large bowl; add all remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Let stand in cold water overnight (add ice). Pack into clean quart canning jars.
Add to each quart 1/8 teaspoon powdered alum, 1 clove of garlic, crushed, and 2 heads of dill.

title: mexican delight
directions: Brown meat.
Add garlic salt and pepper.
Drain meat and add soup, tomatoes and onion.
Mix together.
Layer with corn tortillas and meat mixture and top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bluefish special
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan.
Lightly brown chopped mushrooms, chopped hazelnuts and breadcrumbs.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Stuff bluefish; bake in a 450° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wrap in foil. Cook on grill about 15 minutes.

title: myrtle's zyrtles
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan with butter.
Layer ingredients, starting with crumbs.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: spoon bread(maryland style)
directions: Stir 2 cups boiling water slowly into sifted meal until smooth.
Add salt and eggs.
Then add milk and baking powder last. Pour into sizzling baking dish into which has been melted 1 tablespoon of Crisco.
Bake in hot oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken into 8-inch square baking dish. Layer cheese over chicken.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over cheese layer.
Mix melted butter and stuffing mix.
Layer on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix puddings together as directed on box.
Add sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
In 9 x 13-inch pan or long dish, alternate vanilla wafers, bananas and creamed mixture, ending with creamed mixture.
Use remaining 1/2 of Cool Whip as topping.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and chop.
Saute in margarine and garlic 3 minutes to brown.
Add sausage until well browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients until heated through.
Stuff each mushroom cap and heat at 350° about 3 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper; drain.
Add beans and Tabasco into dressing.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes and onion. Crush taco chips.
Add ground beef and beans to vegetables and mix.
Add taco chips and dressing.
Toss.
Add seasoning for flavor as desired.

title: edible finger paint
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water; cook over low heat. Stir constantly until thick.
Divide in 4 to 5 portions and add different colorings.
Great for small children.

title: popcorn snowman
directions: You will need colored paper or yarn.

title: paella salad
directions: In large skillet, cook chicken and shrimp in oil until tender; remove and set aside.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add Carolina rice; stir until opaque.
Add saffron, broth and lemon juice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes until rice is tender.
Add chicken and shrimp.
Chill several hours.
Serve on green.
Garnish with olives, avocado and tomatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften	cream
cheese.	Mix all ingredients using 1 cup chopped pecans.
Form
into
ball and roll in remaining cup of pecans, crushed.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef in hot oil.
Place uncooked noodles on top of meat. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over noodles, moistening well.
Do not stir.
Bring to a boil, then turn heat low.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Use a 3 or 4 quart container.

title: taco salad(serves 12)
directions: Saute onion in large skillet.
Add ground beef and brown. Drain grease.
Add drained kidney beans to skillet with cooked ground beef.
Simmer until thoroughly heated.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Fold into egg-zucchini mixture.
Pour into 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.

title: eggless hillbilly cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except soda and flour.
Boil for one minute,
then
add
flour and soda.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: buttermilk pie in corn flour crust
directions: Sift cornmeal and flour together.
Cut in shortening.
Add cheese. Finish as any other pie crust.

title: green chili quiche
directions: Chop or dice chilies and layer in bottom of pan.
Cover with cheese.
In a bowl, mix biscuit mix, milk and eggs and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.
Not too spicy.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and place in casserole dish.
Then add the topping.

title: amish-style chicken casserole
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, start preparations.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
In large skillet, melt butter and cook mushrooms until tender.
Blend in flour; gradually add broth, milk, salt and pepper, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened.
Preheat oven to 350° sometime during these preparations.
In greased 2 1/2 quart casserole dish, combine noodles, chicken and sauce.
Top with cheese and bake for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce for an army
directions: Rinse each can with 1/2 can of water and mix all ingredients together.
Simmer for 5 hours.

title: blitz torte
directions: Cream 1/2 cup of sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, salt, flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 2 large, ungreased, 10-inch layer cake pans.

title: honey yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve honey in 1/4 cup warm water.
Scald milk and add butter, honey and salt, let butter melt.
Cool milk mixture to lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast, then flours.
Mix well.
Knead until satin smooth.
Place in buttered bowl; cover and let rise two hours, or until doubled in bulk. Punch down and form into round balls about the size of a golf ball.
Place separately on buttered cookie sheet or close together in buttered round pan. Cover and let rise again about 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes about 2 dozen. These freeze well.

title: ham strata
directions: Butter both sides of bread slices.
Place 8 slices in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Add half the ham and cheese.
Top with remaining 8 slices of bread and cover with remaining ham and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard together and pour mixture over layered dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for one hour or until top is golden brown.
If desired, mix crushed corn flakes with melted butter and sprinkle over casserole before baking.
May be made 1 to 2 days ahead.
Chopped onion may be added to ham and cheese.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mi cake mix, 1 egg and butter (will be thick).
Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour over layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: pavlova
directions: Bring egg whites to room temperature.
Beat until they are really stiff; they look dry.
Mix together sugar and cornstarch. Add to egg whites and mix in very fast.
Add vinegar and beat only enough to mix.
Form mixture in a mounded circle on aluminum foil, greased very lightly.
Flatten top.
Heat oven to 300°, turn down to 225°; bake for 45 minutes.
Turn oven off for 30 minutes; do not open during this time.
Turn upside down on plate.

title: maple walnut cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, shortening, maple syrup, vanilla and maple extract in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Drain peaches.
Arrange peaches and cherries in sugar mixture.
Mix cake as directed on box; spread batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes until cake tests done with a toothpick.
Let stand 5 minutes, then turn upside-down on cookie sheet.
Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin praline squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine all filling ingredients.
Beat at medium speed 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cornflake drops
directions: Bring the sugar and syrup to a rolling boil.
Add peanut butter.
Stir and mix well.
In a large mixing bowl, pour ingredients over the cornflakes and coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out flesh.
Reserve skins.
Saute garlic in the stock until softened, about 3 minutes.
Mash the potato with the warm milk, yogurt, garlic, pepper, paprika and cabbage.
Stuff the potato mixture into the reserved skins.
Place the potatoes in a baking dish and bake them until heated through, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, pour water over oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add sugars and butter, stirring until butter melts.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in flour, soda, cocoa and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in half of chips.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with remaining chips and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a saucepan on low-medium heat, stir in soup and sour cream and spices.
Mix well.
Do not boil.
Keep warm.
Spread 2 to 3 tablespoons soup mixture onto tortilla. Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons chicken pieces.
Roll up.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
After all tortillas are in pan, pour remaining soup mixture over tortillas and sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese.
Jalapeno peppers may be sprinkled on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: christmas pudding borrowed from henry vii("plum duff")
directions: It is traditional for family to each take a turn stirring, and each make a wish.

title: ribbon oyster scallop
directions: Heat oyster stew very slowly until thawed.
Lift out oysters and set aside.
Drain liquids from canned oysters and mushrooms into stew pan.
Heat.
Saute oysters and mushrooms in butter and set aside.
Stir crackers into stew and heat.
Stir in seasonings, oysters and mushrooms and layer whole mixture into baking dish. Melt butter in saucepan and mix with crushed crackers and alternate rows of parsley and butter-cracker mix on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix fruit, sugar, tapioca and almond extract in a bowl.
Fill pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate with fruit mixture.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Cover pie with top crust.
Seal and flute edge.
Cut several slits to permit steam to escape.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes only.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar
and cornstarch together.
Mix egg yolks with milk. Add
to
sugar mixture with salt.
Cook, stirring until thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar and peanut
butter until crumbly.
Place 2/3 of this in bottom of baked
pie shell.
Add filling and top with whipped cream or
Cool Whip.
Sprinkle
rest of peanut butter mixture over top.

title: oven barbecue
directions: Lay chicken on 13 x 9-inch pan and cover with barbecue sauce and onions.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over and baste.
Return to oven for 30 more minutes.
Remove chicken from oven.
Place biscuits in sauce, then place on top of chicken. Return to oven until biscuits are done (usually 10 minutes).
Serve with corn-on-the-cob and string beans.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into unbaked pie shell at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix string beans, mushroom soup and chopped mushrooms together in casserole dish.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: anita's hunter stew
directions: Brown meat, using no seasonings, in a skillet or Dutch oven. (I use a deep fat fryer/slow cooker combination.) Turn down heat. Add soup mix and condensed soup.
Water can be added (a small amount) to make a thinner sauce.
Cover and simmer until meat is done.
Serve with rice, mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: perfect apple dumplings
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; cook 5 minutes, then set aside.

title: squash
directions: Mix together. Top with bread crumbs. Add butter. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix all other ingredients together with margarine. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions for 5 minutes. Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream and carrots in large bowl and fold in cooked squash and onions. Blend stuffing mix and butter in separate bowl and place 1/2 the mixture in baking pan. Spoon squash mixture over stuffing and sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over the top. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: chruschedi(polish)
directions: Put all ingredients, except flour, in a bowl and beat until well mixed.
Stir in flour and chill 1/2 hour; roll mixture very paper thin on floured board.
Cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Make a small lengthwise slit in the center.
Roll 1 end through slit to make a bow.
Deep fry in hot oil or shortening until golden brown. Dish with powdered sugar.
Cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits and roll into mixture of cinnamon and sugar. (Easier to put sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl with lid and shake.)
Spray Bundt pan with Pam and place biscuits in it.
Put leftover sugar and cinnamon in melted butter and mix.
Pour over biscuits.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Invert on plate and slice or pull apart with fingers.
Great for holidays.

title: favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the sugar with the margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until light and fluffy.

Mix together flour, soda, baking powder and salt. When well mixed, add slowly to sugar mixture. Stir in vanilla. Add oatmeal and coconut alternately while beating mixture. Stir in nuts and drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes until cookies are golden brown.
For crisp cookies, bake longer; for chewy cookies, bake less.
Makes
5 dozen cookies.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water until done, about 10 minutes.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in pan.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Put cheese and cauliflower in a greased 2-quart casserole dish and spoon sauce over top.
Combine stuffing, 1/4 cup water and 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Mix well and put over cheese sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients; pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake pulls away from pan.

title: ziti and smoked sausage salad
directions: Saute sausage in a frying pan, using a little oil, if necessary, over high heat for 5 minutes.
Drain fat and combine sausage in a large bowl with remaining ingredients.
Toss well with the vinaigrette and serve at room temperature.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli for 5 minutes. Drain. Add all other ingredients to broccoli and pour into buttered casserole dish. Spread crumbs on top and bake for 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes in an 8 or 9-inch pan.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion and okra in hot drippings until okra ceases to rope, about 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes and stir in remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves four.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix in order and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased and floured loaf pan.

title: no bake cake
directions: Leave ice cream out to get soft.
Break up angel food cake and put in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix ice cream, milk and instant pudding together.
Pour over angel food cake.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Top with Cool Whip and Heath candy.
Cut and serve.

title: dodie's potato casserole
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients and pour into greased pan (10-inch square Corning is fine).
Top with cornflake crumbs mixed with melted margarine (or any other crunchy topping you might prefer; crushed potato chips would be good).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, mayonnaise and water; beat.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: easy tender country style steak
directions: Salt and pepper cube steak; roll in flour and fry until brown on both sides in melted shortening.
Put steak in large pan after browning (9 x 13-inch Pyrex works well).

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cook cake mix as directed.
Puncture with fork and pour 1 cup Hershey's syrup over cake.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Break up cake until crumbly and mix pudding.
Put in deep glass container, layering as follows:

title: creamy white fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt coating with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar real well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine flour and spices; mix together, then add to the butter mixture.
Add this to all the fruit, nuts and preserves that have been chopped.
Line a tube cake pan with brown paper; grease the paper with cooking oil.
Add the cake to this pan; cover with wax paper and tie the paper down with a string.
Put the rack in the pressure cooker that has about 3 cups of water in the bottom of the cooker.
Cook on 10 pounds pressure for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Lay 1 can of crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Press seams together.
Mix first 4 ingredients together and spread over dough in pan.
Lay last can of crescent rolls on top, again pressing seams together.
Brush top with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix shortening and salt into flour, as you would for pie crust. Add milk.
Will make a stiff dough.
Roll thin and cut as desired. Drop dumplings into boiling broth, one by one, so they do not stick together.
Cook slow for 12 to 15 minutes (covered).
Do not stir or remove cover until ready to serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and stem mushrooms.
Dry.
Mix the cheeses and the onion; stuff into mushroom caps.
Dip in melted butter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until cheese is brown.

title: my favorite cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large mixing bowl; pour in Bundt cake pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Bring noodles to boil.
Drain and place in casserole dish. Add sauces.
Put cheeses and pepperoni on top.
Bake in oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cream the butter; gradually add sugars.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well each time.
Add nuts and raisins; drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: low-fat cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake pie crust and cool on rack. Preheat oven to 400°.
Make filling.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in the eggs, cornstarch and vanilla. Add sour cream and mix well.
Pour into crust and bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn off oven; leave in oven with door open for 3 hours. Refrigerate for 8 hours.
Top with fruit.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs together; add flour, allspice, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, soda, salt, buttermilk and nuts.
Stir in figs.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients (don't use mixer).
Pour into 3 small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt both packages of chips. Blend in peanut butter. Stir in peanuts and marshmallows.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until set.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole. Dot with butter and sprinkle with cracker crumbs or Durkee fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well; add zucchini.
Spread in a 13 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cut in squares and serve warm.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour into beaten eggs.
Add milk and butter.
Stir in vanilla and coconut.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Stir together egg whites, water, corn syrup and vanilla.
Mix well, then add Basic Baking Mix.
Spread batter evenly in 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan coated with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over batter.
Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over batter (water should cover mixture).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°; cool slightly.
Spoon into dessert plates warm or refrigerate to serve cold.

title: garbanzo and rice soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, saute the onion and garlic in the butter until translucent.
Add the garbanzos and the liquid from the can, the chicken stock, rice, parsley and tomato paste.
Heat just to a boil.
Add the cheese and serve at once.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: pool room slaw
directions: Mix and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal. This is good to eat on hot dogs.

title: texas brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour and sugar. In a heavy saucepan, combine butter, shortening, coffee or water, and cocoa. Stir and heat to boiling. Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar in the mixing bowl. Add, buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla. Mix well using a wooden spoon or high speed on electric mixer. Pour into a well buttered 17 1/2 X 11 inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or until brownies test done in the center. While brownies bake, prepare the frosting.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Pound cutlets; set aside.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine bread crumbs, flour and grated cheese; set aside.
Heat in a skillet 1/2 cup olive oil.
Dip cutlets into egg mixture, then into crumb mixture.
Add cutlets to skillet and slowly brown on both sides.
Arrange cutlets in a baking dish. Pour spaghetti sauce over cutlets, then top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with oregano.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serves 6. Serve over spaghetti.

title: milky way bundt cake
directions: Melt candy bars and butter in double boiler; beat briskly and cool.
Blend cake mix, pudding and water.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add candy mixture and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool cake 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: foolproof cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Place this mixture on top of butter.
Pour fruit in the center of batter.
No need to stir.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tater tot bake
directions: This gravy can be made from grease where chicken, rabbit or steak has been fried.
Pour off all but 1 cup of the grease, leaving crumbs.
Add enough flour to take up all grease and brown until deep brown.
Add milk to make thin gravy, stirring constantly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until thickened and serve over hot homemade biscuits or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yvonne's strawberry daiquiri
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend in ice and sugar to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add green pepper, onion, corn and tomato soup.
Let
simmer
for
a
little while.	Pour into a casserole dish.
Mix	cornmeal to make a thin batter and pour over mixture. Bake at 400° until cornbread is brown.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Add milk to cream cheese and beat.
Add instant pudding to mixture.
The mixture will be like a paste; if it is too stiff, add more milk.
Add whipping cream, sugar and vanilla; stir well. Add whipping cream mixture with pineapple mixture slowly into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and chill until ready to serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put pudding and milk in a Tupperware bowl with a tight lid. Put on lid and shake.
Spoon out into a dish and microwave until barely warm.
Stir and add bananas.

title: cookie icing
directions: Place sugar and milk in bowl.
Stir until mixed thoroughly. Add corn syrup; mix well.
For filling in areas, use thinned icing (add small amounts of light corn syrup until desired consistency is reached).

title: bacon wrapped chicken breasts
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in bacon and secure with a toothpick. Bake in 350° oven until done.
Place breast in a casserole dish. Mix soup and sour cream together.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbling.

title: quick potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix potatoes, cheese, soup, salad dressing, onion and pepper.
Spoon into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with combined crushed corn flakes and margarine.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken ala paris
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken breasts.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix thoroughly the soup, mushrooms, sour cream and sherry; pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve with wild rice.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Mix together by hand until a dough forms.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove and while warm, toss cookies in plastic bag of confectioners sugar.
Repeat in about 20 minutes.
Store in cool place.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out on counter and cut the dough with a cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until tender.
Drain and cool.
Add onion, green pepper and green onions.
Mix with one tablespoon of oil.
Beat together in a large bowl 1/2 cup of oil, sugar, tomato soup, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Then mix all ingredients together.
Let stand a few hours, then refrigerate. Real good to make a day or 2 before serving.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix well in casserole. Add pieces of chicken, skin side up. Bake in a 375° oven about 1 1/2 hours.

title: boyd's chicken special
directions: In large mixing bowl, add chicken, cooking sherry, celery, carrots, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Mix together and let marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
One hour before cooking, take the bowl out of the refrigerator and add the remaining ingredients.
Let sit for 30 minutes and put in a large, deep baking dish or pan.
Bake in 400° oven until chicken is tender. Serve with rice or pasta.

title: lemon custard cake
directions: Tear the baked cake in pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Beat until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Spread this over the cake.
Spoon pie filling on top of this and chill.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1/4 cup hot butter in skillet, cook onion; add mushrooms and green pepper and cook until tender. Remove vegetables and set aside.
In same skillet, heat remaining butter.
Add rice and brown slightly, stirring, over low heat. Stir in vegetables and thyme.
Heat chicken broth to boiling. Stir into rice-vegetable mixture, then turn into 1-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves; grease pans.

title: "dirt"
directions: Make the pudding.
Add the thawed topping and the cookies. Spoon into new, clean flowerpot.
Add a plastic flower on top and gummy worms.
Serve with a new, clean trowel.

title: coco lopez coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package and bake.
Remove from oven and punch holes with wooden spoon handle.
Pour cream of coconut in holes.
Sprinkle cake with coconut and cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut. This uses a lot of coconut.

title: carrot rice ring
directions: Cook carrots and onion in butter until tender; combine with rice and flour.
Blend soup, egg and seasonings; add to rice mixture.
Turn into greased 8-inch ring mold.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before inverting on serving platter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: angel food creamed cake
directions: Let the cream cheese get soft in bowl.
Mix with milk and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Break up the cake.
Fold into cream mixture. Put in glass bowl. Chill overnight. Top with canned cherry pie filling (or any filling of your choice).
Fresh sliced strawberries with a little sugar makes a good topping.

title: heath bar trifle
directions: Make cake and pudding according to package directions.
Cut cake into chunks and layer in trifle bowl alternately with pudding, Cool Whip and crushed candy.

title: thousand island pickles
directions: Heat together, but do not boil.
Pack into jars and seal while very hot.
It is better to make 4 quarts at a time.

title: steamed pumpkin pudding
directions: Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Blend flour, baking powder, salt, soda and spices.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour milk and pumpkin.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart mold.
Steam 1 3/4 hours.
Cool a few minutes; loosen from sides of mold. Remove from mold.
Serve warm.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar; press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spreading evenly.
Bake in a 400° oven for 6 or 7 minutes, watching carefully; let cool.

title: peach pudding dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Beat in milk and oil until smooth.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange peaches on top.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon; sprinkle over peaches.
Pour water on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: apple dumplings(mary sangster trail's recipe)
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder, 2 teaspoons of sugar, cream of tartar and salt.
Cut in the shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center.
Add milk all at once.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Knead gently on a lightly floured surface for 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll out to about 12 x 14 inches and 1/2 inch thick.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Cook ground beef, ground pork, onion and garlic in heavy Dutch oven or roaster until meat is browned and onion is tender. Drain off excess fat.

Add tomatoes and break up with a fork. Stir in tomato sauce, 1 1/2 tablespoons parsley flakes, the sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and the basil; simmer uncovered 1 hour or until mixture is as thick as a good spaghetti sauce.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Drain browned meat and onion.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer 10 minutes until flavors blend.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well. Make paste with cocoa and food coloring; add to cream mixture. Mix salt, vanilla and buttermilk and add alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Mix soda and vinegar and fold into the mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 2 (9-inch) layer pans, greased and floured.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Cook chocolate pudding as directed on package.
As soon as pudding is done, add package of cake mix, right from the box, into the hot pudding (do not go by cake box directions).
Mix and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish (grease and flour cake pan).
Top with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Cake is moist.)

title: "meskin" dirty rice
directions: In cast-iron pot, heat the oil.
Chop the onion and garlic. Saute in hot oil. Soak bouillon in water to be added later.
Add to sauteed mix the chili powder, jalapeno and rice. Brown. Cut sausage into 1/4-inch cubes and add to mixture.
Add bouillon mixture. Add salt to taste.
Be sure mixture is covered with liquid. Cover pot and place in oven which has been preheated to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Cream the butter with the sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla. Add the dry ingredients; mix.
Add the mashed bananas, nuts and sour cream.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: old-fashioned navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight.
Saute carrots, onion and celery to a golden color in heavy kettle or Dutch oven.
Brown ground beef and drain.
To the vegetables in kettle, add 1 gallon water or stock, if available.
Add 2 medium raw, cubed potatoes and ground beef.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Peel the tomatoes; cut up and add to soup.
Salt and pepper.
Yields 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt 1/2 cup of margarine and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, powdered sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons margarine and spread on top.
Cut while warm into 1-inch squares.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from chocolate pieces.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: In Dutch oven brown beef; drain off fat.
Stir in other ingredients; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork teriyaki
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork strips and mix well.
Add pork to marinade; cover and marinate in refrigerator at least one hour.
Thread meat onto skewers.
Broil or grill, turning frequently 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve with rice, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix well.
Add enough milk (a little at a time) to make a thin paste.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add remainder of milk gradually until well mixed.
Add oleo.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until real thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until filling is real smooth.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, whip the cream and place on top of pie.

title: chicken-in-a-pot(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Place carrots, onions and celery in bottom of crock-pot.
Add whole chicken; salt and pepper and add liquid.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or on high for 3 1/2 to 5 hours.
High requires 1 cup liquid.
Remove chicken and vegetables with spatula.

title: sweet 'n' sour pot roast
directions: Combine garlic salt, mustard and pepper; rub over entire roast. In a Dutch oven, brown roast on all sides in oil over medium-high heat; drain. Combine the water, soy sauce, vinegar, honey, celery seed and ginger; pour over roast. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove roast from pan and keep warm.

title: frozen golden punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Combine all ingredients and pour into containers to freeze. Makes about 1 gallon punch.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in bacon grease, garlic and Tabasco.
Score an onion; wrap with bacon.
Place in middle of trash and bake for 2 hours at 250°, stirring frequently.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Layer potatoes on bottom of 9X13 casserole dish.

title: reuben spread or dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased covered casserole.	Bake in
a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serve on party rye or crackers.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and seasoning in oven (do not cook until done).
Mix in bread crumbs, eggs, cheese and drained spinach.
Mix well.
Stuff into partially cooked shells.
Put into casserole dish.
Pour your favorite pasta sauce over top.
Bake until warmed through and noodles are tender.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water together.
Stir in sugar, oil and egg. Add flour; mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Shape into rolls. Let rise.
Cook at 425°.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Brown onions in margarine.
Add other seasonings and cook until tender.
Add shrimp and cook about 20 minutes or until tender.
Season to taste.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in a large casserole.
Top with 2 cups crushed cornflakes and dot with 1/4 cup oleo.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mom's chili
directions: In large kettle or saucepan, brown ground beef.
Drain and add onion; cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Before serving, thicken with 3 tablespoons flour mixed with 1/4 cup water.
Stir until thickened.
Serve with cornbread.
Kids love it!

title: vichy carrots(french recipe)
directions: Just cover with water and simmer on medium flame until no water is left.
Add heaping tablespoonful margarine or butter; stir and serve.

title: orange pecans
directions: Bring sugar, orange juice and pecans to a boil; stir until coated.
Pour on a cookie sheet to cool.

title: simmered beef with shallots
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, cook beef cubes in oil until browned on all sides.
Stir in mushrooms, carrots, shallots, beef broth, wine, and water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover pot, and simmer for one hour.
Top with parsley; serve.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook mixed vegetables and drain well.
Drain beans and rinse. Mix all vegetables together.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt. Add vinegar, water and mustard.
Cook until thick and clear.
Pour over vegetables.
May be made a day ahead of serving.

title: holiday odor punch
directions: Not for consumption!
Mix.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until house smells like Christmas!

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Cook and drain packages of frozen chopped broccoli.
Cube Velveeta and cube 1/2 stick of butter.
Mix together these ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top of broccoli mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in blender.
Slowly add vinegar and celery seed.
Keeps quite a while.
Gets thick and creamy.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple stuffed turkey tenderloins
directions: Combine apple, orange juice, cranberry sauce and marmalade in small saucepan.
Cook until apple is soft but holds its shape. Wipe tenderloins with damp paper towel.
Slice them lengthwise to form pocket.
Spoon half of apple mixture into each pocket.
Secure edges with toothpick.
Cut each tenderloin in half.
Egg should be beaten with water.
Dip tenderloins in egg mixture.
Dredge in crumbs.
Put in casserole dish not touching.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve remaining sauce over turkey.
Serves 4. Also good with chicken breasts.

title: cheese-olive balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together except for olives.
Form dough into small balls with an olive in the center. Bake about 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 4 dozen. Best served hot.

title: cheddar cheese sauce
directions: In microwave, heat milk in 2 cup glass cup for 1 minute on High.
Remove and add cheese and stir to moisten.
Scrape into blender or food processor and puree until smooth.
Return to glass cup.
Heat on High 30 seconds.
Stir and season.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar in bowl, then spread on top.
Top with a little cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna barbecue
directions: Mix together and heat.
Serve on buns.

title: makes its own crust coconut pie
directions: Step 1:
Beat eggs and then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes with electric mixer.

title: june's banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine or butter.
Press into the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate. Mix confectioners sugar, 2 sticks softened butter or margarine and eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes; you may add a little milk to thin; spread on graham cracker crust.
Put sliced bananas on top.
Add in layers the pineapple, frozen strawberries and Cool Whip. Garnish with chopped nuts and cherries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Skin and cut chicken breasts in bite size pieces.
Saute with celery and onions in margarine.
Steam broccoli.
Cook rice until nearly done.
Combine all ingredients in a large baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May be reheated in a microwave.

title: almond-flavored pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 2 baking sheets with vegetable spray.
In a medium bowl, stir together the whole wheat flour, unbleached flour and baking powder.
Cut butter into mixture with a pastry blender until mixture resembles crumbs.
Mix in nuts.
In a small bowl, beat together the eggs and honey.
Add grape juice, extracts and spices. Stir into flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the cheese, then pile lightly into a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole or into individual baking dishes.
Sprinkle lightly with grated cheese.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, soda and salt and add alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts and dates, mixing thoroughly.
Spoon into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or five 16-ounce cans.
Bake loaves in a preheated 350° oven for
60 minutes and cans in a 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out of pans and continue cooling on rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lorretta's southern tea
directions: To Make One Gallon Of Tea:
Put cloves in 1 quart of water. Bring to a slow boil; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour mixture through a strainer (to catch cloves) into a gallon size container. Add teabags; steep 3 minutes.
Add 3 quarts more of hot water to make a gallon.
Sweeten to taste.
Chill.
(Amount of clove can be adjusted to taste.)

title: baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place fryer (whole) on a baking pan or dish.
Pour soy sauce over chicken and try to brush some inside the stomach.
Sprinkle the garlic salt, then the sugar and lastly the ground pepper all around the chicken.
Place pan in the oven and bake, checking occasionally.
Check every 15 minutes until done and when doing so, brush drippings over and around the chicken.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, onion, cheese, celery and mayonnaise.
Top with wafers mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple butter pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat
oven
Combine filling ingredients in order given.
Pour
into pie shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until knife
inserted
from center comes out clean.
Top with streusel topping and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned light fruit cake
directions: Line baking pans with aluminum foil. Use two 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pans or a 10 x 4-inch tube pan or 4 pound-size coffee cans. Have nuts and fruit ready. Save some to decorate top of cake.

title: old fashion coconut pie
directions: Heat butter; add sugar.
Beat and add eggs and all other ingredients.
Blend well and bake in 1 unbaked pie shell at 350°.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and butter and cream well.
Add beaten eggs and flour; mix well.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: croccignoles(an old canadian recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients together until dough is well mixed.
Dough should be fairly firm.
Roll on lightly floured board until dough is about 1/4-inch thick.

title: rice krispies marshmallow treats
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted and well blended.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated. Press mixture evenly into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool completely. Yields 24 squares (each 2-inch square).

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: spicy beans and rice
directions: Bring kidney beans, water and picante sauce to boil in medium saucepan.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with cilantro, if desired. Makes 4 cups or 6 servings.

title: tennessee white chili
directions: Combine broth, garlic and 1 chopped onion in a large pot. Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Saute other onion in oleo until tender.
Add chilies and seasonings.
Mix and add to cooked beans.
Add chicken; simmer to blend flavors, about 1 hour.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook and slice beets. In saucepan, stir cornstarch, sugar, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in water (liquid from canned beets) and vinegar. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute; add beets and heat through. If liquid from canned beets doesn't make 2/3 cup, add water.

title: stuffed pumpkin
directions: Cut top off pumpkin and scoop out.
Simmer in salted boiling water until almost tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Do not overcook. Brown beef and onions; add green, red peppers and garlic.
Cook for 1 minute.
Drain and add balance of ingredients.
Spoon into pumpkin.
Add top and brush with oil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand for 10 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Small pumpkin serves 6 to 8.

title: egg nog(a holiday crowd pleaser)
directions: Beat together egg yolks and sugar.
Add cream and milk.
Stir in cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Whip egg whites until stiff and fold in mixture.
Add rum and then egg whites.

title: salmon chowder
directions: If using canned salmon, discard skin and dark meat.
Cook onions in butter about 5 minutes.
Add salmon, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Add flour mixed with 1 tablespoon of the milk and stir to mix.
Add potatoes and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Garnish with dill.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Set aside.
Toss hot spaghetti with olive oil or butter.
Combine eggs and 1/2 cup shredded Parmesan.
Stir into spaghetti.
Pour spaghetti mixture into prepared pie plate.
Form into a "crust." Spread Ricotta over bottom of spaghetti crust.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Bake uncovered 25 minutes.
Top with shredded Mozzarella. Bake 5 minutes more until cheese melts.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with reserved 1/4 cup shredded Parmesan.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: cinnamon dough figures
directions: Mix applesauce and cinnamon until mixture has the consistency of homemade play dough.
Roll out between layers of waxed paper. Cut out with cookie cutters.
Lay out to dry.
Turn each figure once a day for 7 days.

title: burrito pie
directions: Cook beef until brown, add everything else except cheese and pie shells.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Cover with grated cheese.
Top with other pie shells.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chicken dinner
directions: Empty rice in large shallow casserole or baking dish.
Arrange chicken in single layer over rice. Mix together soups and milk. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over top. Cover pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: quick casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions and drain.
Boil macaroni.
Combine beef and onions with macaroni.
Mix in soup. Pour over casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs or cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cream cheese and Cheddar cheese together.
Add garlic powder.
Mix with sour cream using hands to mix well.
Form into ball.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cool in refrigerator for a little while, then take out and roll in nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sour cream strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Combine remaining ingredients, except for sour cream, with jello.
Pour 1/2 of strawberry mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.
Spread on sour cream.
Pour remaining 1/2 of strawberry mixture on top of sour cream.
Let set.

title: ligaya's hamburger soup
directions: In a large pot heat oil (canola is best) and saute garlic until brown.
Add onions and cook until soft.
Add tomatoes and cook and stir about 2 minutes before adding meat, salt, pepper and oyster sauce.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring frequently to crumble meat.
Add potatoes and cook another 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish and top with crushed crackers.
Pour 1/2 cup chicken broth over casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: melt-in-your-mouth pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add egg, milk and oil.
Cook on a hot grill.
I prepare several Ziploc bags of dry ingredients ahead of time and it is like having an instant pancake mix, except it tastes better.

title: royal red strawberry topping
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Slice berries and mash.
Place sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan, stirring to mix.
Add berries and color and cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils and becomes quite thick.
Remove from pan and set aside to cool for about 10 minutes.
Stir in Amaretto.
Cool completely.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: bob's mussels
directions: In skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add white wine, garlic and mussels.
Cover and cook until mussels are opened, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in tomato, basil and red pepper flakes.
Reduce heat; simmer 2 minutes more.
Makes 2 servings.

title: old-time rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine rice, milk, sugar and salt; pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Add lemon peel, nutmeg and raisins.
Continue baking 1 1/2 to 1 1/3 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding dry with drained pineapple.
Add cottage cheese. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Then serve.

title: mother's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients with an electric mixer.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and cook for 30 minutes at 400° or until done.

title: quick beer bread
directions: Stir together and bake in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Best served warm.

title: turkey roast with garden vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place roast in shallow roasting pan.
Mix butter, thyme, rosemary, garlic and tarragon.
Drizzle 1/2 over roast.
Bake, covered, about 1 hour, basting occasionally, until pop-up thermometer pops (165° to 170°) and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute chopped zucchini onion and shredded carrots in 4 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing mix, chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, sprayed with cooking oil spray.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Line bottom of baking ring with mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients and press firmly into baking ring.
Microwave at High 13 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fried rice
directions: Place rice in wok or pan over medium heat.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add other ingredients; mix well.

title: peanut caramels
directions: Melt caramels in microwave.
Add condensed milk and stir well. Microwave again only enough to mix together.
Add peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator to harden.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip hardened candies into chocolate mixture.

title: dried beef-cheese log
directions: Combine cheese and olives; mix well.
Chill until firm.
Shape mixture into a 10-inch log.
Roll log in chopped beef.
Serve with crackers.
Yields one cheese log.

title: mystery mocha cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into greased 9-inch square cake pan. Combine sugars and cocoa.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour coffee over top. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Mix lightly the peeled and sliced apples with water, cinnamon and salt.
Spread apple mixture evenly in ungreased square pan.

title: reed walden's cranberry jello mold
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; mix well. Add sour cream.
Put in mold; chill and let set overnight. Unmold; garnish with oranges.

title: real good pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour mixture into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set and browned.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in other ingredients; beat until smooth.
Place pan of frosting in bowl of ice water.
Continue beating until spreading consistency. Frosts 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cheese at medium speed for approximately 2 minutes.
Gradually beat at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and soda.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Mix at lowest speed just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings. Spoon batter into greased and floured 13-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: coconut cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese. Add milk and sugar, alternately, beating well. Add vanilla and coconut. Frost cake.

title: taco soup
directions: Saute onions, celery and garlic cloves in an iron skillet. Cook ground beef in a separate cooker until thoroughly done.
Drain fat.
Combine sauteed onions, celery and garlic with cooked ground beef.
Then add your corn, beans, stewed tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add your package of taco mix and Ranch dressing mix and thoroughly stir.
Let simmer until you serve.
The longer, the better.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Combine Karo syrup, white sugar and brown sugar and bring to boil.
Take off heat.
Then add peanut butter, salt and vanilla. Stir.
Stir in 1 to 2 cups corn flakes until all flakes are in. Drop on greased cookie sheet (about 1 teaspoon).
Allow to cool. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream together butter and 1/3 cup sugar.
Blend in flour and press into a 10-inch spring-form pan to form crust.
Cream together the cream cheese, vanilla, 1/4 cup sugar and egg. Spread mixture over crust.

title: cube steak deluxe
directions: Cut steak into serving-size pieces.
Saute steaks, mushrooms, onion and garlic powder until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat one hour or until steaks are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: grilled salmon with salsa picante
directions: Place salmon steaks in a shallow pan. Sprinkle both sides with the lime juice, salt and pepper. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and let marinate for 30 minutes, at room temperature.

title: corned beef appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
After ingredients are mixed, chill several hours.
Spread on fancy crackers.

title: raisin nut bread
directions: Combine yeast, dry milk, honey, molasses, salt and oil in a large bowl.
Stir in warm milk (very warm).
Blend well about 30 seconds.
Blend the flour (both) in a medium size bowl.
Stir 1 1/2 cups of flour mix into the yeast mixture.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in another 1/2 cup of flour; beat 1 minute. Beat in raisins, walnuts and remaining flour.
Should be a heavy sticky dough.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Turn dough into a well-greased pan.
Cover and let rise for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Pour in 1/2 of cracker crumbs.
Layer of chicken, layer of water chestnuts.
Mix sour cream and the 3 soups together.
Add mixture of soups.
Layer of cracker crumbs.
Top with melted butter, drizzled.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can make ahead of time overnight.
Use only butter and expensive crackers are essential.

title: breakfast in a biscuit
directions: Cook bacon in a frypan until crisp.
Drain and set aside. Beat eggs in a small bowl.
Coat frypan with a no-stick cooking spray and scramble eggs until soft.
Set aside.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut steak into small even pieces.
Remove fat and gristle. Melt butter in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add meat and cook over hot fire until meat is well browned on all sides.
Add salt, pepper, paprika and onions.
Stir in flour until smooth and thickened.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Add potatoes; cover and continue cooking until meat and potatoes are tender.
Serves 4.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: green beans with basil
directions: Place beans and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook, uncovered, for 7 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain; add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: vegetable melts
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Sprinkle with cheese over English muffin halves.
Broil 5 1/2 inches from heat for 1 minute or until cheese melts.
Top each half with vegetable mix and sprouts.
Serve immediately.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Place butter in saucepan; melt in low heat and remove. Combine flour, sugars and salt in bowl.
Stir in milk.
Pour into butter saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir in beaten eggs and cook for 2 minutes.
Add meringue and bake 10 minutes.

title: swiss bar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter, white sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add egg yolks, baking powder and baking soda. Press in a greased 11 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and chocolate chips; press down.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Slowly add 1 cup brown sugar.
Spread over chips, nuts and dough.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: decorating frosting
directions: Whip at low speed until well blended.

title: a meal in a loaf
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise; carefully scoop out inside and break into bite-size pieces.
Combine ground chuck and onion in a large saucepan; cook until meat is brown.
Stir in soup and bread pieces.
Spoon meat mixture into bottom half of bread shell and cover with top half of bread shell.
Wrap loaf in foil; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
To serve, cut into slices.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chili cheese squares
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Blend in salt, baking powder, flour and Tabasco.
Add cheeses and butter.
Mix only until blended.
Stir in green chilies by hand.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, almonds, water chestnuts, onions, lemon juice, eggs and pepper. Add mayonnaise and toss.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle generously with cheese and potato chips. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: crabbies
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on English muffins.
Place under broiler until toasted.
Cut into bite size pieces and serve.

title: yummy apple sticks
directions: In a small mixer bowl, stir together the brown sugar, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add eggs, peanut butter, milk and vanilla.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed, just until combined.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Spread mixture in a well-greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Lightly press apple slices, peel side up, into mixture, spacing evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.
Cut into small sticks.
Remove from pan.
Dip in powdered sugar.
Makes 30 to 35 sticks.

title: lei lanis stir-fry teriyaki steak
directions: In a large bowl, combine soy sauce, sugar, garlic and ginger. Add steak and stir.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Stir occasionally.
Place cooking oil in a large skillet or wok.
When hot enough to splatter water, add steak and marinade.
Stir constantly until done, approximately 6 to 10 minutes.
Serve with hot cooked rice.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Chop onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Add corn, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix into crumbled corn bread.

title: party punch
directions: Mix in order as listed.
Serves 24.

title: apple salad
directions: Pour pineapple juice all over apples and bananas.
Add rest and stir gently.

title: beef stew
directions: Place meat in a casserole dish.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Do not uncover while cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine slightly beaten eggs and sugar.
Blend in chocolate, butter, salt and
pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Filling will set while cooling.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add nuts and raisins; mix.
Add sliced apples and mix.
Place in well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and frost.

title: lime cream jello salad
directions: In double boiler, dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add marshmallows; dissolve into jello mixture.
Stir until dissolved; set aside to cool.
Mix the cottage cheese, crushed pineapple with juice and the chopped nuts.
Add to cooled jello mixture. Refrigerate until it thickens.
Add 1 tub Cool Whip and serve.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Put into blender and mix well.
If not sweet enough, add a little more sugar.
Put snow in individual bowl and pour enough mixture over it.
Mix as you like it.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chips; stir until melted. Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8-inch or 9-inch pan. Chill until firm.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and garlic until done; drain.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with chips.
Top with hamburger mixture. Mix remaining ingredients (except cheeses).
Pour over hamburger. Top with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: boston brown bread
directions: This recipe is easily doubled.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Mix melted margarine with Ritz cracker crumbs; spread on top of soup mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Beat well; add crushed bananas and nuts, flour and soda.
Bake in loaf pan in a moderate oven (325°), 30 to 45 minutes, depending on thickness. Serve plain or ice with 7 minute icing.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Combine eggs, oil and defrosted strawberries and mix well.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in 350° preheated oven 60 to 70 minutes until done.

title: 7-layer southwest dip
directions: Line 12-inch platter with lettuce.
Stir black beans, pepper and onion.
Spoon on top of lettuce.
Dollop sour cream atop bean mixture.
Sprinkle with jalapeno and lime peel.
Drain excess liquid from salsa.
Stir in avocado.
Spoon over sour cream layer. Sprinkle cheese over this.
Top with olives and cilantro.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Contains 4 grams of fat per serving.

title: new england apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream together margarine and both sugars. Beat in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
In a medium bowl, combine next 5 ingredients. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir to combine thoroughly.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spoon into a greased 10-inch Bundt pan or 3 medium size loaf pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out almost clean (because of the apples, the toothpick will be moist).
When cooled, can dust with confectioners sugar.
Be sure to refrigerate any leftovers.
Serves 16.

title: thanksgiving cranberry relish
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring 1 cup water to a boil; remove from heat.
Add gelatin and sugar; stir until dissolved.
Add ReaLemon and remaining water.
Chill while preparing remaining ingredients.

title: creamy cocoa taffy
directions: Butter 9-inch square pan; set aside.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, cocoa, salt and vinegar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Add evaporated milk and butter.
Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, to 248° or until syrup forms a firm ball that does not flatten when dropped and removed from cold water.
(If using a candy thermometer, do not let bulb set on bottom of saucepan.) Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Cool until lukewarm and comfortable to handle.
Butter hands; immediately stretch taffy, folding and pulling until light in color and hard to pull.
Place taffy on table; pull into 1/2-inch wide strips (twist 2 strips together, if desired).
With buttered scissors, cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: mock danish(sugar-free)
directions: In small round microwavable bowl that has been sprayed with PAM. Beat softened cream cheese with remaining ingredients, except jam. Then swirl in jam for a marbled effect. Microwave for 2 minutes on High. If still runny in the middle, microwave for an additional 20 seconds or so until set. Run a knife around the edge. Turn upside down onto plate and let cool slightly. Eat and enjoy!

title: bernie's dip
directions: Chop beef into 1-inch square pieces.
Mix the cream cheese, onions, sour cream and milk until well blended.
Add beef to mixture.
Spread in a 9-inch pie plate.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Add sugar and vinegar to drippings.
Drain beans; slice and separate onions into rings.
In large casserole, begin layering of beans, almonds, bacon and onions until last layer is complete.
Pour drippings over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Best when refrigerated overnight.

title: coconut-chocolate chip dessert
directions: Put enough milk into a dish/bowl to dip each cookie.
Dip cookies (crunchy are better) on both sides long enough to make them slightly soft.
Place softened cookies in container and top with a thin layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chocolate chops (I use the small ones) and coconut.
Continue to layer until you have the desired amount.
Top with a final layer of Cool Whip.

title: cherry pudding(from dad's cousin, lulu brott shaffer)
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream together.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together three times and add to shortening-sugar mixture, in small amounts, alternately with the milk.
Pat this batter into a greased baking dish.
Pour cherry-boiling water mixture over batter and dot with bits of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and serve at once.
When pudding is done, fruit will be in the bottom of the dish in a thick syrup, with the cake part on top.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, cake mix and coconut.
Pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apples on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples. Beat egg and sour cream.
Pour over apples.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1 2/3 cups sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and roll biscuits in this mixture; drop into Bundt pan.
In a pan, mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bring this to a boil; pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Put apples in buttered 8-inch square baking dish. Mix cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle on apples. Arrange bread slices over apples. Combine egg and oleo; mix well. Pour over bread. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves, then add oil and set aside. Mix all other ingredients, then pour liquid mixture over it and mix everything well. Refrigerate a couple of hours or overnight. Good on hot dogs.

title: sweet corn with peppers
directions: Heat oil & butter in skillet. Add garlic, onions, peppers, and corn. Sprinkle with salt & pepper. Cook 2 minutes. Very Good!

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolk and cream well.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast, then add all the other ingredients, beating thoroughly. Shape into rolls. Place in greased pan. Cover and let rise over night in a warm spot. Bake in heated oven until brown. The dough only has to rise one time.

title: paper thin squash pickles
directions: Cover
squash,
bell
peppers and onions.
Soak in real cold water
and
cup
salt; soak for 1 hour.
Drain real good. While soaking, put sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric in large boiler; let come to boil.

title: tuna pot pie
directions: Mix pie crust.
Use store-bought pie crust or can use canned biscuits.
Line bottom of casserole dish if using pie crust.
Mix all ingredients, adding 3/4 can water.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into lined dish.
If using pie crust, roll out a top and put on top of mixture, slitting top to allow steam out.
If using biscuits, line top of mixture with biscuits.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until brown.
When using biscuits, make sure they cook through.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet 1-inch apart. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and let sit in oven for 30 minutes.
(Don't open oven after putting kisses inside, not even to peep.)

title: ham and corn fritters with sage
directions: Cut ham into small dice.
Chop scallion.
Cut butter in 4 chunks.
Bring butter, water, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper to a boil in a saucepan and boil just until butter melts. Remove from heat and stir in flour all at once.
Stir over low heat just until mixture is smooth and comes away from the sides of the pan in a ball.
While still hot, transfer to a food processor or mixing bowl and process or beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in the ham, scallion, corn and sage.
Heat oil in large pot to 375°. Drop the dough by heaping tablespoonfuls into the hot fat and fry until golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels before serving.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water.
Boil until thick and clear. Beat egg whites, gradually adding sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Add vanilla to cornstarch mixture.
Spread over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Make graham cracker crust:
Crush graham crackers; mix with melted butter.

title: chili tamale casserole
directions: Unwrap tamales; place in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Combine chili and onion; spread evenly over tamales.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; continue baking 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook onions until tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in cornstarch, salt, bouillon, gravy sauce and 1 1/2 cups water; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Keep mixture warm.

title: cumberland sauce
directions: Simmer wine, pepper, brown sugar, raisins and dry mustard for 8 minutes in saucepan.
Add cornstarch and simmer 2 minutes. Add orange juice, lemon juice, currant jelly and orange marmalade. Simmer until well mixed.
Refrigerate in a glass jar.
Will keep for up to one month in refrigerator.

title: fruit nut bars
directions: Spread nuts in 2 large pans.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat in flour and vanilla.
Pour over nuts.
Cut up candied fruit in small bits and pour over batter. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry garlic and onions until soft in hot oil in heavy pan.
Add beef; cook until crumbly, stirring.
Mix in salt and pepper. Blend tomato paste with water and spices.
Stir in beef mixture. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Pour a thin layer of sauce into oblong pan.
Add 1/3 noodles.
Add more sauce.
Add 1/3 cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set in pan for 15 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: salmon pie(microwave)
directions: Grease 9-inch glass deep-dish pie plate.
Mix rice, Parmesan and egg.
Press into prepared pie plate to form crust; set aside.

title: potatoes
directions: Mix well.
Put into baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Make two and freeze one for later.

title: roladen(german beef rolls)
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups water.
Set aside.
Slice bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Sprinkle top round with pepper.
Spread with mustard.
Distribute onion and bacon evenly.
From short end, roll up and fasten with round toothpicks.
Coat pan with oil. Brown rolls on all sides.
Remove.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut tops
of
kernels
from
cobs
with
a sharp knife. Scrape the
pulp and milk of corn from the cobs.
Fry bacon in large, heavy skillet.
Remove bacon and pour corn into the hot drippings. Cook
at medium heat until corn begins to brown on bottom.
Stir and
add
sugar, salt and pepper to taste.	Add the milk and stir again.
Simmer, covered, stirring every once in awhile for 12 to 15 minutes or until corn has thickened and is well done.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake in 350° to 375° oven until done.

title: chocolate chip cookie wreath
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line two 12-inch pizza pans with foil. Cream brown sugar, sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Blend well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Divide dough in half.
Spoon dough in circle on pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Remove from pan.
Decorate if desired.
To make things stick on wreaths, use icing.
Makes 2 wreaths.

title: celebration chicken
directions: Place a long sheet of foil on shallow 10 x 15-inch baking pan or cookie sheet. Arrange chicken in a layer on foil. Combine onion soup, ketchup, brown sugar and water and pour over chicken evenly. Close the foil to make an envelope and seal in juice. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes. Remove chicken to platter and spoon sauce over chicken. Serves 4.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown the hamburger, celery and onion and season.
Add rest of ingredients except chow mein noodles and pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
The last 20 minutes, sprinkle the chow mein noodles over the top.

title: creamed chicken and biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease all sides and bottom
of an 11 x 17-inch baking dish. Chop the onion. Heat butter in small nonstick skillet and saute onion until tender.

title: fudge betty's recipe
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt. Add milk. Cook on medium heat, stirring at first to bubbly boil. Put in candy thermometer. Cook until soft-ball, stirring some. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla until it loses its gloss and appears to thicken. Pour onto platter. Best cut in squares while still warm.

title: layered salad
directions: Place shredded lettuce in bottom of serving bowl.
Follow with layers of shrimp, sliced water chestnuts, frozen peas, celery and radishes.
Shortly before serving, frost with mayonnaise, shredded Swiss cheese and sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer celery and onion in the butter, then add the first 5 ingredients.

title: marguerites
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add remaining ingredients in the order given.
Fill small buttered tins 2/3 full of mixture and place pecan nut meats on each.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add milk and sugar.
Mix well by hand.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 1 hour before cutting.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix as listed in a "large" dishpan.
Drop 1/2 cup dough flattened on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Takes 6 cookies to a sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 75 to 80 cookies.

title: lemonade for 100 people
directions: Boil 4 cups water and sugar for 10 minutes.
