Cool the syrup. Add lemon juice.
Stir in pineapple.
Add oranges and 4 gallons water.
Chill.
Serve over ice.

title: "stuffed" pork chops
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until softened.
Combine celery and onion with bread cubes and seasoning.
Stir in enough cream of mushroom soup to hold it together; set aside.
Combine remaining soup with 1/2 can milk; set aside.
Brown pork chops on both sides in skillet.
Transfer pork chops to baking dish.
Mound stuffing mix in center of each pork chop.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla until creamy.
Blend in egg quickly.
Mix together the flour, salt and baking soda and stir into creamed mixture by hand.
Add chips. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine or butter in 10 x 13-inch Pyrex or metal pan.
Dust pieces in 1/3 cup flour, 1 1/2 teaspoon paprika, 1/4 teaspoon poultry seasoning and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Place chicken in butter, skin side down, and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add to pan 1 cup rice, 1/2 cup chopped green pepper, 1/2 cup chopped onion in dish.
Pour over this 3 cups hot chicken broth.
Put chicken on top and return to 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered.

title: diabetic fruit bars
directions: Boil together dates, prunes, raisins and water.
Add margarine. Mix together eggs, soda, salt, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Add batter to fruit mixture.
Bake in 7 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop everything up in blender, then boil on stove until thick (about 2 hours).
Then put in containers; can freeze.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and milk together.
Add flour, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour over rhubarb that has been placed in an unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and bake at 350° for approximately one hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg whites with a few grains of salt; add sugar and cream of tartar.
Spread on pie.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: creamed fish
directions: Scald milk.
Put onion, parsley and thyme in a cheesecloth and cook slowly in the milk one hour or more.
Remove seasoning.
Melt the butter.
Add the flour and brown for a few minutes.
Add the milk to the butter and flour with a bit of salt and the nutmeg and egg yolk.
Cook the halibut with salt and lemon juice.
Flake when done.
Layer some sauce in the bottom of a baking dish, then a layer of fish.
Season lightly with salt and pepper, then add more sauce and fish and sauce again.
Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs and cover with Parmesan cheese.

title: coconut pie
directions: Bake pie crust at 350°.
Set aside.
Beat 4 egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Set aside for meringue.

title: chess cookies
directions: Mix well.
Pour onto dough.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: apricot-pineapple jam
directions: Soften apricots; cover apricots with boiling water and stand overnight or place apricots and 3 cups of water in a bowl.
Cover and microwave on High for 12 minutes, then add the additional 2 cups of boiling water and cook as for recipe.
When softened, bring apricots and water to boiling point.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Boil rapidly until setting point is reached (20 to 25 minutes).
Place in sterilized jars and seal with wax.

title: frozen breakfast fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put into serving paper cups.
Fill 2/3 full.
Put into freezer.
Take out 15 minutes before serving.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill dough.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Melt butter; blend in cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Heat to boiling over low heat; stir constantly.
Stir into slightly beaten egg yolks.
Return to heat and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
Makes 2 cups. Sprinkle coconut in bottom of pie shell.
Add custard.

title: salsa sauce(california style)
directions: Mix together in blender.
Serve with tortilla chips or use in chili.

title: orange fluff
directions: Slice oranges and drained pineapple on paper towels.
Mix with cottage cheese mixture and fold in whipped topping.
Can be made a day ahead.
Serves 12.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the sugar, eggs, oil, zucchini and vanilla together, then add the flour, nuts, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
You can freeze the fresh zucchini and also you can freeze the bread.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in cherry pie filling, chocolate morsels and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9-cup fluted or 10-inch plain tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake cake for one hour.
Cool for ten minutes, then remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: strawberry whip pie
directions: Wash and hull the strawberries, then slice in quarters.
Save several perfect strawberries for garnish, if desired.
Just before serving, whip the cream in a chilled bowl with a chilled beater until stiff.
Add lemon juice, then beat in sugar.
Fold the strawberries lightly and turn into the pie shell.
Top with the selected whole strawberries.
Serve at once.
Makes 5 servings.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage and set aside.
Bake pie shell until brown. Place cheese slices in bottom of pie shell and cover with sausage. Combine eggs and milk, beating well, and pour over sausage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine ingredients excluding nuts and coconut and blend well. Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish and top with nuts and coconut. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: baked potato ring
directions: Combine grated raw potatoes, melted butter, beaten eggs, green onion, bacon, salt and paprika, mix well.
Place in a well buttered bundt pan and pour the milk over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle the grated sharp cheese over the potatoes.
Return to oven and bake until cheese has melted and browned.

title: jean's chicken & rice
directions: Mix the above ingredients together in a casserole dish. Brush cut up chicken with worcestershire sauce. Salt and pepper. Place on top of rice, cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: summer salad
directions: Drain all fruit and pour into a large bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Cover and chill.

title: cowboy rice
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees.
In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef until browned, drain.
Add onions & pepper.
Cook and stir until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook about 2 minutes.	Pour into casserole dish. Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix crust; pour on top of chicken mixture.
Bake in oven 30 minutes or until crust is brown at 375°.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes, celery and onion in 1 cup water until celery is tender.
Add all seasonings and cream cheese.
Puree in blender until creamy texture and return to low heat, not allowing to come to boil.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Put rice in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Add chopped onion, then put chicken in dish.
Cover with soup and water mixture.
Cover casserole.
Bake at 335° for about two hours until brown.

title: * mock lasagna casserole *
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, garlic salt, pepper, basil and 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer half each of macaroni, cottage cheese, shredded cheese and meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 370° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spanish tomato rice
directions: In a 10 inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove.
Pour off half the fat.
In remaining fat, cook chopped onion and green pepper until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, water, rice, chili sauce, salt, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top.
Trim with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender. Remove from bone. Combine soup and sour cream in separate bowl. Place chicken in an oblong dish. Pour soup and sour cream mixture over chicken.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Cut cake in squares.
Then mix strawberries and glaze.
Let sit for a few minutes.
Mix well.

title: ham and bean soup(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain. Cover beans with fresh water, 6 to 8 cups. Add all ingredients and let simmer (after coming to a boil) for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally. (You may add 1 to 2 tablespoons sugar to help the taste if too garlicky or acidy from the tomatoes.) Enjoy!

title: three step fruit topped cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pink cranberry freeze(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Soften the cream cheese, blend in salad dressing.
Add sugar, fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream to which powdered sugar and vanilla have been added.
Pour into a loaf pan and freeze at least 6 hours.
Tastes delightful with turkey and keeps in freezer indefinitely.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw the potatoes and combine the rest.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are tender.
During the last 15 minutes, put crushed crackers on top.
Serves 12 to 15 and cooks best in 2 casserole dishes.

title: sliced cheese biscuits
directions: Combine sausage, flour, cheese, shortening and milk in bowl, mixing well.
Shape into long rolls.
Cut into slices. Place slices on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.
Yields 24 servings.

title: best and easy chocolate fudge(makes 5 pounds to freeze or for gifts)
directions: Place chocolate chips, butter and marshmallow in a large bowl. In a heavy 4-quart pan bring to a boil sugar and evaporated milk, stirring constantly.
When mixture reaches a full boil cook for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over chocolate mixture.
Stir until well blended and holds its shape.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into 15 x 10-inch pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: punch
directions: Freeze all ingredients, except ginger ale. When time to serve, take out of freezer and add ginger ale.

title: mexican salad
directions: Tear lettuce and put into a large bowl.
Sprinkle cheese on top of lettuce.
Meanwhile, brown beef, season with Chili powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Pour over lettuce and cheese, stir to mix.
(Hot meat will melt the cheese.)
You may add tomatoes, avocados, etc.
Eat with Dorito chips.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Spray 10 or 12-inch skillet with nonstick spray.
Put potatoes, water, margarine and milk in skillet.
Season to taste. Cover and cook over medium to low heat, stirring occasionally. Add onion, carrots, celery and salad olives with pimientos. Sprinkle with chopped, dried parsley.
Cover and continue cooking, stirring occasionally,
to keep from scorching and to evenly cook potatoes and other vegetables.
Serves 10 to 12.
This may also be cooked in microwave.

title: bride's punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients; stir well.
A frozen ring for the center may be made from mandarin oranges, cherries, pineapple and water.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Cook to soft ball stage, 236°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and walnuts.
Stir until grainy and put in buttered pan or on waxed paper.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in bowl until smooth.
Pour in a greased pizza pan.
Brown hamburg; drain well.
Sprinkle hamburg over crust mixture and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust looks done.
Take out of oven and add pizza sauce and cheese.
Turn oven down to 325° and bake pizza for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and sauce is hot.

title: light cherry cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix in oleo.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°; set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend ingredients together and roll into balls.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.
Serve plain or with your choice of sauce.

title: rice fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: never fail hot water pie crust
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening.
Stir until melted.
Add dry ingredients and stir until absorbed and mixture forms a ball. Roll out between sheets of waxed paper.
Makes two (9-inch) crusts or 3 smaller crusts.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown first 2 ingredients together and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry meat. Add onion, garlic, chili powder and salt.
Melt cheese. Add tomatoes (canned) and chili peppers.
Combine meat mixture and cheese mixture. Serve on top of Fritos, then top with lettuce and cherry tomatoes.

title: camp stew
directions: Boil meats together until done; debone.
Chop very fine.
Boil potatoes and onions together, until tender.
In large pot, heat corn, peas and tomatoes until hot.
Add meat and catsup.
Add hot sauce to taste.
Simmer for an hour or so, keeping it stirred very well.
Simmer slowly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda; set aside.
Mix oleo, sugar, egg, vanilla and almond.
Blend in flour mixture.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick and cut out cookies.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: cranberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pat cranberries, pecans and 1/2 cup sugar into bottom of an 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: holy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Frost, if desired.
For mixing icing, use Proverbs 23:14.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges reserving up to two cups of liquid.
Add pudding to juice and mix as directed on pudding box. Pour over fruit. Add cherry pie filling and nuts.
Chill. Shortly before serving, add sliced bananas. Serves 10 to 12.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill.

title: scalloped broccoli
directions: Put broccoli in buttered casserole with 1/2 stick margarine and Velveeta cheese.
On top, put Ritz crackers, crushed with other half stick margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: With beater mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning. Place in pie plate or dish with high sides; chill.
Add 1/2 jar salsa, green peppers, tomatoes, cut up olives (chopped), chillies (optional) and shredded lettuce.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: icebox cookies(granny cookies)
directions: Mix sugar, Wesson oil, eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices which have been sifted together.
Add nuts last. After mixture has been well blended, shape into roll in desired size.
Roll in wax paper and freeze until you desire to bake. Slice thin.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Put all in mixing bowl and beat vigorously. Pour on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pie supreme
directions: Place 2 pints of cleaned sliced berries in pie crust.
Crush the third pint of berries and mix with sugar.
Cook for 5 minutes. Thicken with cornstarch.
Add butter to melt.
Pour mixture over berries in pie shell and let cool.
Chill and serve with whipped topping.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix together in bowl.
When well mixed, drop by teaspoons on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° until golden brown, about 8 to 9 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken off of the bone. Stir soups and canned milk together. Add all the ingredients together in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake at 450° until browned on top and bubbly.

title: spinach bread
directions: Fry the spinach with garlic, salt and pepper in a little olive oil.
When almost done, add chopped olives to the fried spinach. Layer spinach on rolled out dough.
Top with cheeses, as desired. Roll into jelly roll shape.
Place on a lightly floured pan with seam on the bottom and the ends turned under.
Lightly oil dough top, then make 3 diagonal slits across top with knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: jewish kolachki
directions: Mix well and form into 8 balls.
Chill overnight.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 1 hour in tube pan at 350°.

title: mom's potato candy
directions: Boil the potato until completely cooked. When done, while potato is hot, peel and mash it in a bowl.
Add confectioners sugar and knead. Roll it thin on waxed paper.
Spread a thin layer of peanut butter over entire circle of potato mixture.
Roll it up in jelly roll fashion. With waxed paper around it, chill 30 minutes. Slice and store in airtight container.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, mashed bananas and nuts. Then add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Put in cool oven at 300° for 1 hour.
If the oven is already hot, let batter stand in pan before cooking.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Remove chicken from bones and chop.
Mix melted margarine with bread crumbs; add broth that has been reserved after boiling chicken.
Mix in soup to desired consistency, adding more broth if desired.
Add milk.
Alternate bread crumbs with crumb mixture. Bake at 325° for approximately 25 minutes.
Feeds 6.

title: ginger ale punch
directions: Mix fruit juices and sugar or syrup.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: chicken almond vermicelli
directions: Cook vermicelli in boiling, salted water (2-quarts plus 1 tablespoon salt) until tender, yet firm, 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain.

title: vegetable mozzarella
directions: Mix vegetables together in 2-quart container.
Spread cheese in a thick layer on top.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving so cheese firms up.

title: spicy butternut squash pie
directions: Peel squash.
Slice in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Cut into slices.
Place in saucepan and cover with water.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until tender and drain.
Puree pulp in food processor or mash thoroughly.
Set aside 2 cups squash puree. Store remainder in refrigerator for later use (for up to 5 days). Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Sieve mixture.
Pour 1/2 into each pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Let cool.
Serve with thickened vanilla spiced icing mixture, if desired.

title: quick supper buns
directions: Either
use
this or your own recipe for biscuit dough. Roll out
to
about
1/3-inch in thickness.
Dot with butter, sprinkle with sugar, dust with cinnamon, currants and raisins and roll
the same as a jelly roll.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch pieces. Place
with
cut edges on well-greased pan.
Bake in moderate oven.
Remove
from pan
at once and we assure you that there won't be any left for the next meal.

title: 1-2-3 cheese straws
directions: Combine cheese and margarine.
Add flour and pepper.
Force through cookie press or cookie gun with star design into long strips on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Store in closed container.

title: pesto
directions: Drop basil in simmering water to tenderize; squeeze dry. Place all ingredients, except cream, in food processor or blender. Blend well.
Lightly blend in cream must before serving.
Toss with pasta.

title: poison cookies
directions: In a saucepan mix raisins, water and soda, boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat, set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine sugar, eggs, butter (melted) and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and baking powder, mix until blended, stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: zuppa di funghi(cream of mushroom soup)
directions: Clean mushrooms and chop.
Melt butter in medium-size saucepan over low heat.
Add chopped mushrooms and cook for about 8 minutes.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Gradually add chicken broth.
Stir until thick.
Add milk and seasonings.
Heat through. Add egg yolk, stir well.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: slovenske kolacky
directions: Combine scalded milk, sugar and shortening. Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast. Stir well with mixing spoon.
Add flour alternately with eggs as follows:
1 cup flour, alternately with 1 egg, repeat and end up with 1 cup flour.
Stir well after each addition.
Let rise for 6 hours in a cool place.

title: pickled okra
directions: Place okra, stem side up, in jars.
Place garlic and pepper on top of okra.
Bring alum, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour over okra and seal.
Don't open this up until 8 weeks have gone by.

title: carrot ring mold
directions: Boil carrots in sweetened water until tender, then mash as well as possible.
Add other ingredients; pour into a buttered ring mold.
Place mold in a pan of hot water.
Bake in a moderate oven for about 30 minutes.
Can be served with creamed peas, adding 1/2 cup of finely cut blanched almonds to peas.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a baking dish.
Mix together the melted margarine and stuffing mix.
Pour over the chicken mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato kibbee
directions: Put potatoes and seasoning in large bowl and mix.
Knead in bread crumbs.
Add mint, parsley and onion.
Knead well.
Place in oiled baking dish.
Press down well.
Cut into squares or diamonds.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs, paprika and 1/2 cup oil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Add remaining ingredients. Bake 350° for 45 min.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Make a paste of food coloring anad cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add milk, alternately, with sifted flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Mix vinegar and soda together.
Blend in (do not beat) soda mixture to batter.
Bake at 350° in two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool in pans on racks for a few minutes. Turn out on rack and while still warm, split cakes with a thread, making 4 layers.
Chill before frosting.

title: hot milk cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs about 5 minutes on high until thick. Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy. Combine dry ingredients; add to batter with vanilla.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
In saucepan, heat milk and butter just until margarine melts.
This may be done in microwave.
Add to batter, beating until combined.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake is done.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: creamy fruit jumble
directions: Put fruit, walnuts, coconut and marshmallows in mixing bowl. Fold in sour cream.
Add sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon to taste. Extra sour cream or whipped cream may be added for extra creaminess.
Serves 6.

title: squash muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Measure 2 cups squash.
Combine squash, eggs and margarine, stirring well, then combine sugar, flour, baking powder and salt
in a mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center and stir in the squash mixture until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen after baking.

title: herb casserole bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a warm bowl and stir until butter is melted and all ingredients are well mixed.
Stir in cheese.
Add 3 cups flour and mix well.
Beat in remaining 1 1/4 cups flour.
Cover bowl with damp towel and let rise 45 minutes or until batter doubles in size.
Stir down; beat 1/2 minute or 25 strokes.
Turn into buttered casserole dish (1 1/2 to 2-quart). Sprinkle top with grated Romano cheese.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
Serve warm with pasta dishes.

title: clifford tea cookies
directions: Cream together the brown sugar and shortening.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Form two long, thin rolls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Let stand in refrigerator for a while.
Turn out; slice thin.
Bake in a 400° oven.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, rolled oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in walnuts, chocolate and peanut butter chips.

title: cottage pudding cake
directions: Heat butter, 3 cups milk and sugar slowly to a boil.
Combine 1/2 cup milk, eggs, salt, cornstarch and flavoring; beat well. Pour hot mixture into the egg mixture; mix well.
Return mixture to stove.
Heat on low until thick.
Make yellow cake following directions on box.
Serve cake with pudding mixture.
Serve with topping warm.

title: squash - rice casserole
directions: Mix
all
together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mock pate
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and liver sausage, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with rye or pumpernickel bread or assorted crackers.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Fry hamburger.
Layer sliced potatoes, sliced onions, hamburger and mushroom soup.
Repeat until casserole is nearly filled.
Add 1/3 cup of milk.
Cover generously with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: 2 chocolate pies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Add egg yolks.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put popped corn in large bowl.
Mix sugar, water, syrup, salt, and butter in sauce pan.
Cook until 250° or until a few drops form a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and food color if desired.
Pour in thin streams over corn stirring to mix well.
Butter hands and shape into balls or other shapes.
Cool on waxed paper. 12-15 balls (depending on size).

title: imitation lobster
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil (except haddock).
Drop in sliced haddock (slice into 4 pieces).
Boil for 15 minutes.
Melt butter for dipping.

title: hot cakes or waffles
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Add milk and water.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in oil. Mix flour and milk mixture a little at a time.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Line bottom with bread. Brown sausage.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese on bread.
Mix together eggs, milk, dry mustard and onion.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
(You can refrigerate this overnight if you need to.)

title: sliced green tomato pie
directions: Make pastry for 2-crust pie.
To peel tomatoes easily, immerse in boiling water until skins will slip off (about 3 minutes). Blend together the sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, flour and lemon juice in bowl.
Toss in green tomatoes.
Place in pastry lined 9-inch pie pan.
Adjust top crust and flute edges; cut vents. Bake in hot oven at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes, until tomatoes are soft and crust is browned.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine the first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Cut in shortening.
Combine buttermilk and soda; add to dry ingredients, stirring until all ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto a floured board.
Knead lightly 10 to 12 times.
Roll dough out; cut with cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and drain the fat.
Stir in the soup, sugar, salt, pepper, garlic and tomatoes.
Gently stir in 1 1/2 cups of the cheese and all the macaroni.
Place in a casserole dish and top with the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until the cheese is completely melted.

title: crepes
directions: Beat all ingredients with hand beater until smooth.
Continue to add milk until batter no longer forms peaks.
For each crepe, lightly oil 7 or 8-inch skillet; heat over medium-high heat until oil runs like water.
Pour scant 1/4 cup batter into skillet; quickly rotate skillet until batter covers bottom.
Cook until light brown; turn and cook other side until light brown.
Place crepes on wax paper until cool.
Stack and cover with Saran Wrap to prevent them from drying out.
Crepes may be frozen or filled immediately.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve the Kool-Aid and sugar in boiling water.
Add juice and ginger ale.
Mix together and serve chilled.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute
onion and garlic in oil until
tender.
Add
beef and sausage.
Stir in sauce and paste, water,
salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer for half an hour, stirring occasionally.
Mix Ricotta cheese and eggs in a bowl.
Cover bottom of lasagna pan with cooked noodles.	Top
with
1/3 of meat sauce, 1/2 of Ricotta mixture and
of	Mozzarella slices. Repeat layers and spoon remaining meat
sauce
on
top.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in
oven
for
30 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes before slicing.

title: easy party chicken
directions: Wrap each half of chicken breast with a slice of ham.
Cover bottom of greased 7 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish with torn dried beef.
Place chicken over the dried beef.
Mix mushroom soup with the sour cream and pour over the chicken.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to bake.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 hours.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine peas, corn, celery, green pepper, onion and pimento. Bring to boil the vinegar, sugar, oil and salt. Pour liquid over vegetables and marinate overnight. Serves 20.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: While ribs are browning, simmer remaining ingredients for 15 minutes.
Buy country-style ribs.
Put ribs in shallow pan; do not cover.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup onions over ribs.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes, then pour sauce over ribs.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Baste every 15 minutes.
Add hot water if sauce is too thick.
Cover last 30 minutes of baking.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in cold water.
Cook until tender.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Cook until pepper, onions and tomatoes are tender.
Slice smoked sausage last and cook until this is tender, approximately 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Serve over bed of rice.

title: cran-orange glazed cornish hen
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place hens, breast side up in roasting pan.
Rub evenly with pepper.
Roast about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, in saucepan over medium heat, cook cranberry sauce, orange peel and garlic about 3 minutes until cranberry sauce melts.
Brush hens evenly with sauce.
Continue to roast for 15 minutes longer until hens are tender.
Makes 4 servings (1/2 hen each).

title: joan's pineapple dip
directions: Core and peel pineapple.
Crush 1/2 of pineapple with a potato masher.
Put the crushed pineapple into a saucepan.
Add beaten egg, flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Heat on low heat until thickened.
Allow to cool thoroughly, then add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Cut remaining pineapple into chunks to serve with dip.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly and let stand for 24 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour in an uncooked pie shell. Cook until done, about 40 to 45 minutes, in 400° oven.

title: pineapple carrot raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and spices.
Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.
In a small bowl, combine undrained pineapple, eggs and vanilla. Add liquid mixture to flour mixture. Stir just until moistened. Batter will be lumpy.
Do not overmix.
Stir in margarine.
Spoon batter evenly into 12 greased 2 3/4-inch muffin cups. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire rack to cool. Makes 12 muffins.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix
in cheese and butter together; add vanilla and 10x sugar.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle topping on top.
Bake until brown on top at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: ham delights
directions: Slice through rolls, separating tops from bottoms.
Cream the oleo, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and chopped onion. Spread tops and bottoms of rolls with creamed mixture.
Add ham and Swiss cheese evenly over the rolls.
Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cut into individual rolls.
Yields 60. Freezes well.

title: skillet macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain, but do not remove from saucepan.
Add rest of ingredients; cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: escalloped tomatoes(servings:  6 to 8)
directions: Saute onion in butter; add bread cubes and sugar.
Cook slowly; stir in tomatoes and seasonings.
Place mixture in buttered shallow casserole and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Place cereal in Fix-N-Mix bowl.
Melt chips, oleo and peanut butter in 1-quart casserole.
Stir to blend.
Pour over cereal and gently stir to coat.
Add powdered sugar to bowl, place seal (burp it) and shake until cereal is well coated.
Let dry slightly before storing in a plastic container.

title: stew beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in baking dish with glass cover.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Then bake 2 hours at 300°. Serve over rice.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese, margarine, vanilla and salt on low speed until smooth.
Beat in cocoa.
Beat in powdered sugar, 1 cup at a time, until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Press firmly in ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.
Cut into squares about 1-inch square.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes about 50 pieces.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Place crackers in
single
layer
in pan.
Cook butter, sugar and pecans over
medium
heat until mixture boils.
Pour over crackers in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: quick crescent pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan. Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles. Press rectangles over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of prepared pan to form crust. Seal perforations. Bake crust at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: play dough ii
directions: Blend 1 cup of love with 1/2 cup of kindness.
In small portions alternately add:
1 cup of appreciation and 3 cups of pleasant companionship into which has been sifted, 3 teaspoons of deserving praise.
Flavor with 1 teaspoon carefully chosen advice. Lightly sift a pinch of sorrow.
Pour with tender care into small clean hearts and bake until well matured.
Turn out on the surface of society.
Humbly invoke God's blessing and it will serve all mankind.

title: blueberry buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal. Combine egg and buttermilk, add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients ar moistened.
Stir in blueberries.
Turn dough out onto heavily floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush warm biscuits with glaze. Yields 15 biscuits.

title: chocolate oreo dessert
directions: Prepare and pour over cream cheese mixture; refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream; garnish with crushed Oreos and cherries.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: Mix thoroughly and sprinkle with awareness.
Bake in moderate oven of everyday life, using as fuel all the grudges and past unpleasantness.
Cool.
Turn out onto a platter of cheerfulness. Garnish with tears and laughter.
Don't forget to have one of the children say the blessing - Oh, Heavenly Father, we thank Thee for the food and remember the hungry.
We thank thee for health and remember the sick.
Thank thee for friends and remember the friendless.
May these remembrances stir us to service that thy gifts to us may be used for others.
Amen.

title: clam dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and garlic salt until smooth.
Fold in clams and onions.
Chill and serve with vegetables, crackers and or chips.

title: sausage-n-cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Melt cheese and mix all ingredients together.
Heat until hot.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on the package; rinse and drain. Marinate overnight in lemon juice, Accent and oil.
The following day, add the rest of the ingredients and mix in mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: irresistible brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour, Nestle cocoa, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla extract.
Stir with a spoon until batter is well blended and smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels and nuts, if desired.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels. Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until set.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: pineapple meringue pie
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine sugar, flour and salt in medium saucepan.
Stir in crushed pineapple, sour cream, egg yolks and lemon juice.
Then add pineapple syrup last before starting to cook.
Then cook over medium heat until mixture is thick.
Cover and cool to lukewarm.
Pour into baked crust and top with meringue.
Brown at 325°.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together (may be mixed in blender).
Store in airtight containers until ready to use.
Use 1 to 2 tablespoons per cup boiling water.

title: taco chicken
directions: First, place thawed chicken in a deep dish.
Next, sprinkle the entire package of taco seasoning over the chicken.
Thoroughly cover the chicken portions with the seasoning by rotating them individually, then pour the two tablespoons of melted butter over the chicken pieces.
Place the dish into a preheated oven at 400° and bake for 45 minutes, or until cooked.
Sprinkle the cheese over the chicken approximately 15 minutes before completion.

title: butter bean soup
directions: Cook butter beans and ham together until done.
Then add rest of ingredients and bring to a slow boil.
Let cook 30 more minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: racioppi's pasta marinara
directions: Heat oil and saute garlic, onion and tomatoes.
Add in ground beef and raisins, then soy sauce.
Cook until brown and tender. Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Serve over rice.
Great with fried bananas and fried eggs.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, syrup, salt and melted butter. Combine well and add pecans and vanilla. Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake in oven at 350° until firm, about 45 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell and cool.
Wash and hull 4 c strawberries.
Then slice and place in cooled pie shell.
Combine water and cornstarch in sauce pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Continue to cook for 2 mins. over low heat.
All Jell-o and stir until dissolved.
Pour Jell-o mixture while still hot over strawberries and let set.
Top with whipped topping.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Fry shells, a few at a time, for 2 to 3 minutes. Drain.
Place on cookie sheet. Top with Velveeta and broil until cheese melts. Top with remaining ingredients. Yields 8 appetizers.

title: beef taco bake
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add soup, salsa, milk, tortillas and half and half; mix.
Spoon into 2-quart shallow baking dish; cover. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
